44   <span class="s1">__doc__ = \</span>
45   <span class="s2">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
46   pyparsing module - Classes and methods to define and execute parsing grammars 
47   ============================================================================= 
48    
49   The pyparsing module is an alternative approach to creating and executing simple grammars, 
50   vs. the traditional lex/yacc approach, or the use of regular expressions.  With pyparsing, you 
51   don't need to learn a new syntax for defining grammars or matching expressions - the parsing module 
52   provides a library of classes that you use to construct the grammar directly in Python. 
53    
54   Here is a program to parse &quot;Hello, World!&quot; (or any greeting of the form  
55   C{&quot;&lt;salutation&gt;, &lt;addressee&gt;!&quot;}), built up using L{Word}, L{Literal}, and L{And} elements  
56   (L{'+'&lt;ParserElement.__add__&gt;} operator gives L{And} expressions, strings are auto-converted to 
57   L{Literal} expressions):: 
58    
59       from pyparsing import Word, alphas 
60    
61       # define grammar of a greeting 
62       greet = Word(alphas) + &quot;,&quot; + Word(alphas) + &quot;!&quot; 
63    
64       hello = &quot;Hello, World!&quot; 
65       print (hello, &quot;-&gt;&quot;, greet.parseString(hello)) 
66    
67   The program outputs the following:: 
68    
69       Hello, World! -&gt; ['Hello', ',', 'World', '!'] 
70    
71   The Python representation of the grammar is quite readable, owing to the self-explanatory 
72   class names, and the use of '+', '|' and '^' operators. 
73    
74   The L{ParseResults} object returned from L{ParserElement.parseString&lt;ParserElement.parseString&gt;} can be accessed as a nested list, a dictionary, or an 
75   object with named attributes. 
76    
77   The pyparsing module handles some of the problems that are typically vexing when writing text parsers: 
78    - extra or missing whitespace (the above program will also handle &quot;Hello,World!&quot;, &quot;Hello  ,  World  !&quot;, etc.) 
79    - quoted strings 
80    - embedded comments 
81    
82    
83   Getting Started - 
84   ----------------- 
85   Visit the classes L{ParserElement} and L{ParseResults} to see the base classes that most other pyparsing 
86   classes inherit from. Use the docstrings for examples of how to: 
87    - construct literal match expressions from L{Literal} and L{CaselessLiteral} classes 
88    - construct character word-group expressions using the L{Word} class 
89    - see how to create repetitive expressions using L{ZeroOrMore} and L{OneOrMore} classes 
90    - use L{'+'&lt;And&gt;}, L{'|'&lt;MatchFirst&gt;}, L{'^'&lt;Or&gt;}, and L{'&amp;'&lt;Each&gt;} operators to combine simple expressions into more complex ones 
91    - associate names with your parsed results using L{ParserElement.setResultsName} 
92    - find some helpful expression short-cuts like L{delimitedList} and L{oneOf} 
93    - find more useful common expressions in the L{pyparsing_common} namespace class 
94   &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

173      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_ustr(obj):</span>
174          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;Drop-in replacement for str(obj) that tries to be Unicode friendly. It first tries 
175             str(obj). If that fails with a UnicodeEncodeError, then it tries unicode(obj). It 
176             then &lt; returns the unicode object | encodes it with the default encoding | ... &gt;. 
177          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
178          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(obj</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">unicode):</span>
179              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">obj</span>
180  
181          <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
182              <span class="s0"># If this works, then _ustr(obj) has the same behaviour as str(obj), so</span>
183              <span class="s0"># it won't break any existing code.</span>
184              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">str(obj)</span>
185  
186          <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">UnicodeEncodeError:</span>
187              <span class="s0"># Else encode it</span>
188              <span class="s1">ret = unicode(obj).encode(sys.getdefaultencoding()</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">'xmlcharrefreplace'</span><span class="s1">)</span>
189              <span class="s1">xmlcharref = Regex(</span><span class="s2">r'&amp;#\d+;'</span><span class="s1">)</span>
190              <span class="s1">xmlcharref.setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t: </span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\\</span><span class="s2">u' </span><span class="s1">+ hex(int(t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">][</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">:-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]))[</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">:])</span>
191              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">xmlcharref.transformString(ret)</span>
192  
193      <span class="s0"># build list of single arg builtins, tolerant of Python version, that can be used as parse actions</span>
194      <span class="s1">singleArgBuiltins = []</span>
195      <span class="s3">import </span><span class="s1">__builtin__</span>
196      <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">fname </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s2">&quot;sum len sorted reversed list tuple set any all min max&quot;</span><span class="s1">.split():</span>
197          <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
198              <span class="s1">singleArgBuiltins.append(getattr(__builtin__</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">fname))</span>
199          <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">AttributeError:</span>
200              <span class="s3">continue</span>
201              
202  <span class="s1">_generatorType = type((y </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">y </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)))</span>

204  <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_xml_escape(data):</span>
205      <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;Escape &amp;, &lt;, &gt;, &quot;, ', etc. in a string of data.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
206  
207      <span class="s0"># ampersand must be replaced first</span>
208      <span class="s1">from_symbols = </span><span class="s2">'&amp;&gt;&lt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">\'</span><span class="s2">'</span>
209      <span class="s1">to_symbols = (</span><span class="s2">'&amp;'</span><span class="s1">+s+</span><span class="s2">';' </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">s </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s2">&quot;amp gt lt quot apos&quot;</span><span class="s1">.split())</span>
210      <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">from_</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">to_ </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">zip(from_symbols</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">to_symbols):</span>
211          <span class="s1">data = data.replace(from_</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">to_)</span>
212      <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">data</span>

217  <span class="s1">alphas     = string.ascii_uppercase + string.ascii_lowercase</span>
218  <span class="s1">nums       = </span><span class="s2">&quot;0123456789&quot;</span>
219  <span class="s1">hexnums    = nums + </span><span class="s2">&quot;ABCDEFabcdef&quot;</span>
220  <span class="s1">alphanums  = alphas + nums</span>
221  <span class="s1">_bslash    = chr(</span><span class="s4">92</span><span class="s1">)</span>
222  <span class="s1">printables = </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(c </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">string.printable </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">string.whitespace)</span>

224  <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException(Exception):</span>
225      <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;base exception class for all parsing runtime exceptions&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
226      <span class="s0"># Performance tuning: we construct a *lot* of these, so keep this</span>
227      <span class="s0"># constructor as small and fast as possible</span>

269             the location of the exception with a special symbol.

280  <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">ParseException(ParseBaseException):</span>
281      <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
282      Exception thrown when parse expressions don't match class; 
283      supported attributes by name are: 
284       - lineno - returns the line number of the exception text 
285       - col - returns the column number of the exception text 
286       - line - returns the line containing the exception text 
287           
288      Example:: 
289          try: 
290              Word(nums).setName(&quot;integer&quot;).parseString(&quot;ABC&quot;) 
291          except ParseException as pe: 
292              print(pe) 
293              print(&quot;column: {}&quot;.format(pe.col)) 
294               
295      prints:: 
296         Expected integer (at char 0), (line:1, col:1) 
297          column: 1 
298      &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
299      <span class="s3">pass</span>

312  <span class="s0">#~ class ReparseException(ParseBaseException):</span>
313      <span class="s0">#~ &quot;&quot;&quot;Experimental class - parse actions can raise this exception to cause</span>
314         <span class="s0">#~ pyparsing to reparse the input string:</span>
315          <span class="s0">#~ - with a modified input string, and/or</span>
316          <span class="s0">#~ - with a modified start location</span>
317         <span class="s0">#~ Set the values of the ReparseException in the constructor, and raise the</span>
318         <span class="s0">#~ exception in a parse action to cause pyparsing to use the new string/location.</span>
319         <span class="s0">#~ Setting the values as None causes no change to be made.</span>
320         <span class="s0">#~ &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
321      <span class="s0">#~ def __init_( self, newstring, restartLoc ):</span>
322          <span class="s0">#~ self.newParseText = newstring</span>
323          <span class="s0">#~ self.reparseLoc = restartLoc</span>

334      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__(self</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">p1</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">p2):</span>

342  
343  <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">ParseResults(object):</span>
344      <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
345      Structured parse results, to provide multiple means of access to the parsed data: 
346         - as a list (C{len(results)}) 
347         - by list index (C{results[0], results[1]}, etc.) 
348         - by attribute (C{results.&lt;resultsName&gt;} - see L{ParserElement.setResultsName}) 
349   
350      Example:: 
351          integer = Word(nums) 
352          date_str = (integer.setResultsName(&quot;year&quot;) + '/'  
353                          + integer.setResultsName(&quot;month&quot;) + '/'  
354                          + integer.setResultsName(&quot;day&quot;)) 
355          # equivalent form: 
356          # date_str = integer(&quot;year&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;month&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;day&quot;) 
357   
358          # parseString returns a ParseResults object 
359          result = date_str.parseString(&quot;1999/12/31&quot;) 
360   
361          def test(s, fn=repr): 
362              print(&quot;%s -&gt; %s&quot; % (s, fn(eval(s)))) 
363          test(&quot;list(result)&quot;) 
364          test(&quot;result[0]&quot;) 
365          test(&quot;result['month']&quot;) 
366          test(&quot;result.day&quot;) 
367          test(&quot;'month' in result&quot;) 
368          test(&quot;'minutes' in result&quot;) 
369          test(&quot;result.dump()&quot;, str) 
370      prints:: 
371          list(result) -&gt; ['1999', '/', '12', '/', '31'] 
372          result[0] -&gt; '1999' 
373          result['month'] -&gt; '12' 
374          result.day -&gt; '31' 
375          'month' in result -&gt; True 
376          'minutes' in result -&gt; False 
377          result.dump() -&gt; ['1999', '/', '12', '/', '31'] 
378          - day: 31 
379          - month: 12 
380          - year: 1999 
381      &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
382      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__new__(cls</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">toklist=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">name=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">asList=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">modal=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
383          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(toklist</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">cls):</span>
384              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">toklist</span>
385          <span class="s1">retobj = object.__new__(cls)</span>
386          <span class="s1">retobj.__doinit = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
387          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">retobj</span>

430      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__getitem__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">i ):</span>

439      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__setitem__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">v</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">isinstance=isinstance ):</span>

452      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__delitem__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">i ):</span>
453          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(int</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">slice)):</span>

456  
457              <span class="s0"># convert int to slice</span>
458              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(i</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">int):</span>
459                  <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">i &lt; </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
460                      <span class="s1">i += mylen</span>

462              <span class="s0"># get removed indices</span>
463              <span class="s1">removed = list(range(*i.indices(mylen)))</span>
464              <span class="s1">removed.reverse()</span>
465              <span class="s0"># fixup indices in token dictionary</span>
466              <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">name</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">occurrences </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.__tokdict.items():</span>

481      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_iterkeys( self ):</span>

484          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
485              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">iter(self.__tokdict)</span>

530      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">pop( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*args</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">**kwargs):</span>
531          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
532          Removes and returns item at specified index (default=C{last}). 
533          Supports both C{list} and C{dict} semantics for C{pop()}. If passed no 
534          argument or an integer argument, it will use C{list} semantics 
535          and pop tokens from the list of parsed tokens. If passed a  
536          non-integer argument (most likely a string), it will use C{dict} 
537          semantics and pop the corresponding value from any defined  
538          results names. A second default return value argument is  
539          supported, just as in C{dict.pop()}. 
540   
541          Example:: 
542              def remove_first(tokens): 
543                  tokens.pop(0) 
544              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; ['0', '123', '321'] 
545              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).addParseAction(remove_first).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; ['123', '321'] 
546   
547              label = Word(alphas) 
548              patt = label(&quot;LABEL&quot;) + OneOrMore(Word(nums)) 
549              print(patt.parseString(&quot;AAB 123 321&quot;).dump()) 
550   
551              # Use pop() in a parse action to remove named result (note that corresponding value is not 
552              # removed from list form of results) 
553              def remove_LABEL(tokens): 
554                  tokens.pop(&quot;LABEL&quot;) 
555                  return tokens 
556              patt.addParseAction(remove_LABEL) 
557              print(patt.parseString(&quot;AAB 123 321&quot;).dump()) 
558          prints:: 
559              ['AAB', '123', '321'] 
560              - LABEL: AAB 
561   
562              ['AAB', '123', '321'] 
563          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
564          <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">args:</span>
565              <span class="s1">args = [-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
566          <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">kwargs.items():</span>
567              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">k == </span><span class="s2">'default'</span><span class="s1">:</span>
568                  <span class="s1">args = (args[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">v)</span>
569              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
570                  <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">TypeError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;pop() got an unexpected keyword argument '%s'&quot; </span><span class="s1">% k)</span>
571          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(isinstance(args[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">int) </span><span class="s3">or </span>
572                          <span class="s1">len(args) == </span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">or </span>
573                          <span class="s1">args[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self):</span>
574              <span class="s1">index = args[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
575              <span class="s1">ret = self[index]</span>
576              <span class="s3">del </span><span class="s1">self[index]</span>
577              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>
578          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
579              <span class="s1">defaultvalue = args[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
580              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">defaultvalue</span>
581  
582      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">get(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">key</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">defaultValue=</span><span class="s3">None</span><span class="s1">):</span>
583          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
584          Returns named result matching the given key, or if there is no 
585          such name, then returns the given C{defaultValue} or C{None} if no 
586          C{defaultValue} is specified. 
587   
588          Similar to C{dict.get()}. 
589           
590          Example:: 
591              integer = Word(nums) 
592              date_str = integer(&quot;year&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;month&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;day&quot;)            
593   
594              result = date_str.parseString(&quot;1999/12/31&quot;) 
595              print(result.get(&quot;year&quot;)) # -&gt; '1999' 
596              print(result.get(&quot;hour&quot;, &quot;not specified&quot;)) # -&gt; 'not specified' 
597              print(result.get(&quot;hour&quot;)) # -&gt; None 
598          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
599          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">key </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self:</span>
600              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self[key]</span>
601          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
602              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">defaultValue</span>
603  
604      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">insert( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">index</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">insStr ):</span>
605          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
606          Inserts new element at location index in the list of parsed tokens. 
607           
608          Similar to C{list.insert()}. 
609   
610          Example:: 
611              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; ['0', '123', '321'] 
612   
613              # use a parse action to insert the parse location in the front of the parsed results 
614              def insert_locn(locn, tokens): 
615                  tokens.insert(0, locn) 
616              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).addParseAction(insert_locn).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; [0, '0', '123', '321'] 
617          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
618          <span class="s1">self.__toklist.insert(index</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">insStr)</span>
619          <span class="s0"># fixup indices in token dictionary</span>
620          <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">name</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">occurrences </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.__tokdict.items():</span>
621              <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">(value</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">position) </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(occurrences):</span>
622                  <span class="s1">occurrences[k] = _ParseResultsWithOffset(value</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">position + (position &gt; index))</span>
623  
624      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">append( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">item ):</span>
625          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
626          Add single element to end of ParseResults list of elements. 
627   
628          Example:: 
629              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; ['0', '123', '321'] 
630               
631              # use a parse action to compute the sum of the parsed integers, and add it to the end 
632              def append_sum(tokens): 
633                  tokens.append(sum(map(int, tokens))) 
634              print(OneOrMore(Word(nums)).addParseAction(append_sum).parseString(&quot;0 123 321&quot;)) # -&gt; ['0', '123', '321', 444] 
635          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
636          <span class="s1">self.__toklist.append(item)</span>
637  
638      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">extend( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">itemseq ):</span>
639          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
640          Add sequence of elements to end of ParseResults list of elements. 
641   
642          Example:: 
643              patt = OneOrMore(Word(alphas)) 
644               
645              # use a parse action to append the reverse of the matched strings, to make a palindrome 
646              def make_palindrome(tokens): 
647                  tokens.extend(reversed([t[::-1] for t in tokens])) 
648                  return ''.join(tokens) 
649              print(patt.addParseAction(make_palindrome).parseString(&quot;lskdj sdlkjf lksd&quot;)) # -&gt; 'lskdjsdlkjflksddsklfjkldsjdksl' 
650          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
651          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(itemseq</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
652              <span class="s1">self += itemseq</span>
653          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
654              <span class="s1">self.__toklist.extend(itemseq)</span>

663      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__getattr__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">name ):</span>

682      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__iadd__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other ):</span>
683          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">other.__tokdict:</span>
684              <span class="s1">offset = len(self.__toklist)</span>
685              <span class="s1">addoffset = </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">a: offset </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">a&lt;</span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s1">a+offset</span>
686              <span class="s1">otheritems = other.__tokdict.items()</span>
687              <span class="s1">otherdictitems = [(k</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">_ParseResultsWithOffset(v[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">addoffset(v[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">])) )</span>
688                                  <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">(k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">vlist) </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">otheritems </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">vlist]</span>
689              <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">otherdictitems:</span>
690                  <span class="s1">self[k] = v</span>
691                  <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(v[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
692                      <span class="s1">v[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].__parent = wkref(self)</span>
693              
694          <span class="s1">self.__toklist += other.__toklist</span>
695          <span class="s1">self.__accumNames.update( other.__accumNames )</span>
696          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self</span>

698      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__radd__(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other):</span>
699          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">other == </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>

703              <span class="s0"># this may raise a TypeError - so be it</span>
704              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">other + self</span>

712      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_asStringList( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">sep=</span><span class="s2">'' </span><span class="s1">):</span>

715              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">out </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">sep:</span>
716                  <span class="s1">out.append(sep)</span>
717              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance( item</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">ParseResults ):</span>
718                  <span class="s1">out += item._asStringList()</span>
719              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
720                  <span class="s1">out.append( _ustr(item) )</span>

723      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">asList( self ):</span>
724          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
725          Returns the parse results as a nested list of matching tokens, all converted to strings. 
726   
727          Example:: 
728              patt = OneOrMore(Word(alphas)) 
729              result = patt.parseString(&quot;sldkj lsdkj sldkj&quot;) 
730              # even though the result prints in string-like form, it is actually a pyparsing ParseResults 
731              print(type(result), result) # -&gt; &lt;class 'pyparsing.ParseResults'&gt; ['sldkj', 'lsdkj', 'sldkj'] 
732               
733              # Use asList() to create an actual list 
734              result_list = result.asList() 
735              print(type(result_list), result_list) # -&gt; &lt;class 'list'&gt; ['sldkj', 'lsdkj', 'sldkj'] 
736          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
737          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[res.asList() </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(res</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults) </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s1">res </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">res </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.__toklist]</span>

739      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">asDict( self ):</span>
740          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
741          Returns the named parse results as a nested dictionary. 
742   
743          Example:: 
744              integer = Word(nums) 
745              date_str = integer(&quot;year&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;month&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;day&quot;) 
746               
747              result = date_str.parseString('12/31/1999') 
748              print(type(result), repr(result)) # -&gt; &lt;class 'pyparsing.ParseResults'&gt; (['12', '/', '31', '/', '1999'], {'day': [('1999', 4)], 'year': [('12', 0)], 'month': [('31', 2)]}) 
749               
750              result_dict = result.asDict() 
751              print(type(result_dict), repr(result_dict)) # -&gt; &lt;class 'dict'&gt; {'day': '1999', 'year': '12', 'month': '31'} 
752   
753              # even though a ParseResults supports dict-like access, sometime you just need to have a dict 
754              import json 
755              print(json.dumps(result)) # -&gt; Exception: TypeError: ... is not JSON serializable 
756              print(json.dumps(result.asDict())) # -&gt; {&quot;month&quot;: &quot;31&quot;, &quot;day&quot;: &quot;1999&quot;, &quot;year&quot;: &quot;12&quot;} 
757          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
758          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">PY_3:</span>
759              <span class="s1">item_fn = self.items</span>
760          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
761              <span class="s1">item_fn = self.iteritems</span>
762              
763          <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">toItem(obj):</span>
764              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(obj</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
765                  <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">obj.haskeys():</span>
766                      <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">obj.asDict()</span>
767                  <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
768                      <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[toItem(v) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">obj]</span>
769              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
770                  <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">obj</span>
771                  
772          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">dict((k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">toItem(v)) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">item_fn())</span>
773

785      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">asXML( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doctag=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">namedItemsOnly=</span><span class="s3">False, </span><span class="s1">indent=</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">formatted=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
786          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
787          (Deprecated) Returns the parse results as XML. Tags are created for tokens and lists that have defined results names. 
788          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
789          <span class="s1">nl = </span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span>
790          <span class="s1">out = []</span>
791          <span class="s1">namedItems = dict((v[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">k) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">(k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">vlist) </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.__tokdict.items()</span>
792                                                              <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">vlist)</span>
793          <span class="s1">nextLevelIndent = indent + </span><span class="s2">&quot;  &quot;</span>
794  
795          <span class="s0"># collapse out indents if formatting is not desired</span>
796          <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">formatted:</span>
797              <span class="s1">indent = </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>
798              <span class="s1">nextLevelIndent = </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>
799              <span class="s1">nl = </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>
800  
801          <span class="s1">selfTag = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
802          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">doctag </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
803              <span class="s1">selfTag = doctag</span>
804          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
805              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.__name:</span>
806                  <span class="s1">selfTag = self.__name</span>
807  
808          <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">selfTag:</span>
809              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">namedItemsOnly:</span>
810                  <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>
811              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
812                  <span class="s1">selfTag = </span><span class="s2">&quot;ITEM&quot;</span>
813  
814          <span class="s1">out += [ nl</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">indent</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">selfTag</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot; </span><span class="s1">]</span>
815  
816          <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">res </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(self.__toklist):</span>
817              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(res</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
818                  <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">namedItems:</span>
819                      <span class="s1">out += [ res.asXML(namedItems[i]</span><span class="s3">,</span>
820                                          <span class="s1">namedItemsOnly </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">doctag </span><span class="s3">is None,</span>
821                                          <span class="s1">nextLevelIndent</span><span class="s3">,</span>
822                                          <span class="s1">formatted)]</span>
823                  <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
824                      <span class="s1">out += [ res.asXML(</span><span class="s3">None,</span>
825                                          <span class="s1">namedItemsOnly </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">doctag </span><span class="s3">is None,</span>
826                                          <span class="s1">nextLevelIndent</span><span class="s3">,</span>
827                                          <span class="s1">formatted)]</span>
828              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
829                  <span class="s0"># individual token, see if there is a name for it</span>
830                  <span class="s1">resTag = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
831                  <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">namedItems:</span>
832                      <span class="s1">resTag = namedItems[i]</span>
833                  <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">resTag:</span>
834                      <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">namedItemsOnly:</span>
835                          <span class="s3">continue</span>
836                      <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
837                          <span class="s1">resTag = </span><span class="s2">&quot;ITEM&quot;</span>
838                  <span class="s1">xmlBodyText = _xml_escape(_ustr(res))</span>
839                  <span class="s1">out += [ nl</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">nextLevelIndent</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">resTag</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
840                                                  <span class="s1">xmlBodyText</span><span class="s3">,</span>
841                                                  <span class="s2">&quot;&lt;/&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">resTag</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot; </span><span class="s1">]</span>
842  
843          <span class="s1">out += [ nl</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">indent</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;/&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">selfTag</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot; </span><span class="s1">]</span>
844          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(out)</span>

846      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__lookup(self</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">sub):</span>
847          <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">vlist </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.__tokdict.items():</span>
848              <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">v</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">vlist:</span>

853      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">getName(self):</span>
854          <span class="s5">r&quot;&quot;&quot; 
855          Returns the results name for this token expression. Useful when several  
856          different expressions might match at a particular location. 
857   
858          Example:: 
859              integer = Word(nums) 
860              ssn_expr = Regex(r&quot;\d\d\d-\d\d-\d\d\d\d&quot;) 
861              house_number_expr = Suppress('#') + Word(nums, alphanums) 
862              user_data = (Group(house_number_expr)(&quot;house_number&quot;)  
863                          | Group(ssn_expr)(&quot;ssn&quot;) 
864                          | Group(integer)(&quot;age&quot;)) 
865              user_info = OneOrMore(user_data) 
866               
867              result = user_info.parseString(&quot;22 111-22-3333 #221B&quot;) 
868              for item in result: 
869                  print(item.getName(), ':', item[0]) 
870          prints:: 
871              age : 22 
872              ssn : 111-22-3333 
873              house_number : 221B 
874          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
875          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.__name:</span>
876              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self.__name</span>
877          <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">self.__parent:</span>
878              <span class="s1">par = self.__parent()</span>
879              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">par:</span>
880                  <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">par.__lookup(self)</span>
881              <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
882                  <span class="s3">return None</span>
883          <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">(len(self) == </span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">and</span>
884                 <span class="s1">len(self.__tokdict) == </span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">and</span>
885                 <span class="s1">next(iter(self.__tokdict.values()))[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">][</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)):</span>
886              <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">next(iter(self.__tokdict.keys()))</span>
887          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
888              <span class="s3">return None</span>
889  
890      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">dump(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">indent=</span><span class="s2">''</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">full=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>
891          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
892          Diagnostic method for listing out the contents of a C{ParseResults}. 
893          Accepts an optional C{indent} argument so that this string can be embedded 
894          in a nested display of other data. 
895   
896          Example:: 
897              integer = Word(nums) 
898              date_str = integer(&quot;year&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;month&quot;) + '/' + integer(&quot;day&quot;) 
899               
900              result = date_str.parseString('12/31/1999') 
901              print(result.dump()) 
902          prints:: 
903              ['12', '/', '31', '/', '1999'] 
904              - day: 1999 
905              - month: 31 
906              - year: 12 
907          &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
908          <span class="s1">out = []</span>
909          <span class="s1">NL = </span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">'</span>
910          <span class="s1">out.append( indent+_ustr(self.asList()) )</span>
911          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">full:</span>
912              <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.haskeys():</span>
913                  <span class="s1">items = sorted((str(k)</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">v) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.items())</span>
914                  <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">items:</span>
915                      <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">out:</span>
916                          <span class="s1">out.append(NL)</span>
917                      <span class="s1">out.append( </span><span class="s2">&quot;%s%s- %s: &quot; </span><span class="s1">% (indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">'  '</span><span class="s1">*depth)</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">k) )</span>
918                      <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(v</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
919                          <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">v:</span>
920                              <span class="s1">out.append( v.dump(indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">depth+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">) )</span>
921                          <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
922                              <span class="s1">out.append(_ustr(v))</span>
923                      <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
924                          <span class="s1">out.append(repr(v))</span>
925              <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">any(isinstance(vv</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">vv </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self):</span>
926                  <span class="s1">v = self</span>
927                  <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">vv </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(v):</span>
928                      <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(vv</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
929                          <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">%s%s[%d]:</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">%s%s%s&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">'  '</span><span class="s1">*(depth))</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">'  '</span><span class="s1">*(depth+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">vv.dump(indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">depth+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">) ))</span>
930                      <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
931                          <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">%s%s[%d]:</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">%s%s%s&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">'  '</span><span class="s1">*(depth))</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">indent</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s2">'  '</span><span class="s1">*(depth+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">_ustr(vv)))</span>
932              
933          <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(out)</span>

935      <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">pprint(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*args</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">**kwargs):</span>
936          <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
937          Pretty-printer for parsed results as a list, using the C{pprint} module. 
938          Accepts additional positional or keyword args as defined for the  
939          C{pprint.pprint} method. (U{http://docs.python.org/3/library/pprint.html#pprint.pprint}) 
940   
941          Example:: 
942              ident = Word(alphas, alphanums) 
943              num = Word(nums) 
944              func = Forward()

946              func &lt;&lt;= ident + Group(Optional(delimitedList(term)))

950              ['fna', 
951               ['a', 
952                'b', 
953                ['(', 'fnb', ['c', 'd', '200'], ')'],

1012 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">line( loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">strg ):</span>
1013     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;Returns the line of text containing loc within a string, counting newlines as line separators. 
1014        &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1015     <span class="s1">lastCR = strg.rfind(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc)</span>

1031 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">nullDebugAction(*args):</span>

1035 <span class="s0"># Only works on Python 3.x - nonlocal is toxic to Python 2 installs</span>
1036 <span class="s0">#~ 'decorator to trim function calls to match the arity of the target'</span>
1037 <span class="s0">#~ def _trim_arity(func, maxargs=3):</span>
1038     <span class="s0">#~ if func in singleArgBuiltins:</span>
1039         <span class="s0">#~ return lambda s,l,t: func(t)</span>
1040     <span class="s0">#~ limit = 0</span>
1041     <span class="s0">#~ foundArity = False</span>
1042     <span class="s0">#~ def wrapper(*args):</span>
1043         <span class="s0">#~ nonlocal limit,foundArity</span>
1044         <span class="s0">#~ while 1:</span>
1045             <span class="s0">#~ try:</span>
1046                 <span class="s0">#~ ret = func(*args[limit:])</span>
1047                 <span class="s0">#~ foundArity = True</span>
1048                 <span class="s0">#~ return ret</span>
1049             <span class="s0">#~ except TypeError:</span>
1050                 <span class="s0">#~ if limit == maxargs or foundArity:</span>
1051                     <span class="s0">#~ raise</span>
1052                 <span class="s0">#~ limit += 1</span>
1053                 <span class="s0">#~ continue</span>
1054     <span class="s0">#~ return wrapper</span>
1055 
1056 <span class="s0"># this version is Python 2.x-3.x cross-compatible</span>
1057 <span class="s2">'decorator to trim function calls to match the arity of the target'</span>
1058 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_trim_arity(func</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxargs=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1059     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">func </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">singleArgBuiltins:</span>
1060         <span class="s3">return lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t: func(t)</span>
1061     <span class="s1">limit = [</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1062     <span class="s1">foundArity = [</span><span class="s3">False</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1063     
1064     <span class="s0"># traceback return data structure changed in Py3.5 - normalize back to plain tuples</span>
1065     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">system_version[:</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">] &gt;= (</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1066         <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">extract_stack(limit=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1067             <span class="s0"># special handling for Python 3.5.0 - extra deep call stack by 1</span>
1068             <span class="s1">offset = -</span><span class="s4">3 </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">system_version == (</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s4">2</span>
1069             <span class="s1">frame_summary = traceback.extract_stack(limit=-offset+limit-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)[offset]</span>
1070             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[frame_summary[:</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">]]</span>
1071         <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">extract_tb(tb</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">limit=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1072             <span class="s1">frames = traceback.extract_tb(tb</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">limit=limit)</span>
1073             <span class="s1">frame_summary = frames[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1074             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[frame_summary[:</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">]]</span>
1075     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1076         <span class="s1">extract_stack = traceback.extract_stack</span>
1077         <span class="s1">extract_tb = traceback.extract_tb</span>
1078     
1079     <span class="s0"># synthesize what would be returned by traceback.extract_stack at the call to </span>
1080     <span class="s0"># user's parse action 'func', so that we don't incur call penalty at parse time</span>
1081     
1082     <span class="s1">LINE_DIFF = </span><span class="s4">6</span>
1083     <span class="s0"># IF ANY CODE CHANGES, EVEN JUST COMMENTS OR BLANK LINES, BETWEEN THE NEXT LINE AND </span>
1084     <span class="s0"># THE CALL TO FUNC INSIDE WRAPPER, LINE_DIFF MUST BE MODIFIED!!!!</span>
1085     <span class="s1">this_line = extract_stack(limit=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1086     <span class="s1">pa_call_line_synth = (this_line[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">this_line[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]+LINE_DIFF)</span>
1087 
1088     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">wrapper(*args):</span>
1089         <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1090             <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1091                 <span class="s1">ret = func(*args[limit[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]:])</span>
1092                 <span class="s1">foundArity[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
1093                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>
1094             <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">TypeError:</span>
1095                 <span class="s0"># re-raise TypeErrors if they did not come from our arity testing</span>
1096                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">foundArity[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]:</span>
1097                     <span class="s3">raise</span>
1098                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1099                     <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1100                         <span class="s1">tb = sys.exc_info()[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1101                         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">extract_tb(tb</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">limit=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">][:</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">] == pa_call_line_synth:</span>
1102                             <span class="s3">raise</span>
1103                     <span class="s3">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1104                         <span class="s3">del </span><span class="s1">tb</span>
1105 
1106                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">limit[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] &lt;= maxargs:</span>
1107                     <span class="s1">limit[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1108                     <span class="s3">continue</span>
1109                 <span class="s3">raise</span>

1111     <span class="s0"># copy func name to wrapper for sensible debug output</span>

1186     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">copy( self ):</span>
1187         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1188         Make a copy of this C{ParserElement}.  Useful for defining different parse actions 
1189         for the same parsing pattern, using copies of the original parse element. 
1190          
1191         Example:: 
1192             integer = Word(nums).setParseAction(lambda toks: int(toks[0])) 
1193             integerK = integer.copy().addParseAction(lambda toks: toks[0]*1024) + Suppress(&quot;K&quot;) 
1194             integerM = integer.copy().addParseAction(lambda toks: toks[0]*1024*1024) + Suppress(&quot;M&quot;) 
1195              
1196             print(OneOrMore(integerK | integerM | integer).parseString(&quot;5K 100 640K 256M&quot;)) 
1197         prints:: 
1198             [5120, 100, 655360, 268435456] 
1199         Equivalent form of C{expr.copy()} is just C{expr()}:: 
1200             integerM = integer().addParseAction(lambda toks: toks[0]*1024*1024) + Suppress(&quot;M&quot;) 
1201         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1202         <span class="s1">cpy = copy.copy( self )</span>
1203         <span class="s1">cpy.parseAction = self.parseAction[:]</span>
1204         <span class="s1">cpy.ignoreExprs = self.ignoreExprs[:]</span>
1205         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.copyDefaultWhiteChars:</span>
1206             <span class="s1">cpy.whiteChars = ParserElement.DEFAULT_WHITE_CHARS</span>
1207         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">cpy</span>

1223     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">setResultsName( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">name</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">listAllMatches=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">):</span>
1224         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;

1226         of the returned parse results. 
1227         NOTE: this returns a *copy* of the original C{ParserElement} object; 
1228         this is so that the client can define a basic element, such as an

1251     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">setBreak(self</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">breakFlag = </span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>

1269     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">setParseAction( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*fns</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">**kwargs ):</span>
1270         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1271         Define one or more actions to perform when successfully matching parse element definition. 
1272         Parse action fn is a callable method with 0-3 arguments, called as C{fn(s,loc,toks)}, 
1273         C{fn(loc,toks)}, C{fn(toks)}, or just C{fn()}, where: 
1274          - s   = the original string being parsed (see note below) 
1275          - loc = the location of the matching substring 
1276          - toks = a list of the matched tokens, packaged as a C{L{ParseResults}} object 
1277         If the functions in fns modify the tokens, they can return them as the return 
1278         value from fn, and the modified list of tokens will replace the original. 
1279         Otherwise, fn does not need to return any value. 
1280  
1281         Optional keyword arguments: 
1282          - callDuringTry = (default=C{False}) indicate if parse action should be run during lookaheads and alternate testing 
1283  
1284         Note: the default parsing behavior is to expand tabs in the input string 
1285         before starting the parsing process.  See L{I{parseString}&lt;parseString&gt;} for more information 
1286         on parsing strings containing C{&lt;TAB&gt;}s, and suggested methods to maintain a 
1287         consistent view of the parsed string, the parse location, and line and column 
1288         positions within the parsed string. 
1289          
1290         Example:: 
1291             integer = Word(nums) 
1292             date_str = integer + '/' + integer + '/' + integer 
1293  
1294             date_str.parseString(&quot;1999/12/31&quot;)  # -&gt; ['1999', '/', '12', '/', '31'] 
1295  
1296             # use parse action to convert to ints at parse time 
1297             integer = Word(nums).setParseAction(lambda toks: int(toks[0])) 
1298             date_str = integer + '/' + integer + '/' + integer 
1299  
1300             # note that integer fields are now ints, not strings 
1301             date_str.parseString(&quot;1999/12/31&quot;)  # -&gt; [1999, '/', 12, '/', 31] 
1302         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1303         <span class="s1">self.parseAction = list(map(_trim_arity</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">list(fns)))</span>
1304         <span class="s1">self.callDuringTry = kwargs.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;callDuringTry&quot;</span><span class="s3">, False</span><span class="s1">)</span>
1305         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self</span>
1306 
1307     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">addParseAction( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*fns</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">**kwargs ):</span>

1309         Add one or more parse actions to expression's list of parse actions. See L{I{setParseAction}&lt;setParseAction&gt;}. 
1310

1317     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">addCondition(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*fns</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">**kwargs):</span>
1318         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;Add a boolean predicate function to expression's list of parse actions. See  
1319         L{I{setParseAction}&lt;setParseAction&gt;} for function call signatures. Unlike C{setParseAction},  
1320         functions passed to C{addCondition} need to return boolean success/fail of the condition. 
1321  
1322         Optional keyword arguments: 
1323          - message = define a custom message to be used in the raised exception 
1324          - fatal   = if True, will raise ParseFatalException to stop parsing immediately; otherwise will raise ParseException 
1325           
1326         Example:: 
1327             integer = Word(nums).setParseAction(lambda toks: int(toks[0])) 
1328             year_int = integer.copy() 
1329             year_int.addCondition(lambda toks: toks[0] &gt;= 2000, message=&quot;Only support years 2000 and later&quot;) 
1330             date_str = year_int + '/' + integer + '/' + integer 
1331  
1332             result = date_str.parseString(&quot;1999/12/31&quot;)  # -&gt; Exception: Only support years 2000 and later (at char 0), (line:1, col:1) 
1333         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1334         <span class="s1">msg = kwargs.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;message&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;failed user-defined condition&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
1335         <span class="s1">exc_type = ParseFatalException </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">kwargs.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;fatal&quot;</span><span class="s3">, False</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s1">ParseException</span>
1336         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">fn </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">fns:</span>
1337             <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">pa(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
1338                 <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">bool(_trim_arity(fn)(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t)):</span>
1339                     <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">exc_type(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">msg)</span>
1340             <span class="s1">self.parseAction.append(pa)</span>
1341         <span class="s1">self.callDuringTry = self.callDuringTry </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">kwargs.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;callDuringTry&quot;</span><span class="s3">, False</span><span class="s1">)</span>

1344     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">setFailAction( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">fn ):</span>

1346            Fail acton fn is a callable function that takes the arguments

1353            if it is desired to stop parsing immediately.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

1518                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">len(cache)</span>

1554     <span class="s0"># argument cache for optimizing repeated calls when backtracking through recursive expressions</span>
1555     <span class="s1">packrat_cache = {} </span><span class="s0"># this is set later by enabledPackrat(); this is here so that resetCache() doesn't fail</span>
1556     <span class="s1">packrat_cache_lock = RLock()</span>
1557     <span class="s1">packrat_cache_stats = [</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>

1559     <span class="s0"># this method gets repeatedly called during backtracking with the same arguments -</span>
1560     <span class="s0"># we can cache these arguments and save ourselves the trouble of re-parsing the contained expression</span>
1561     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_parseCache( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">callPreParse=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
1562         <span class="s1">HIT</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">MISS = </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1563         <span class="s1">lookup = (self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callPreParse</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions)</span>
1564         <span class="s3">with </span><span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache_lock:</span>
1565             <span class="s1">cache = ParserElement.packrat_cache</span>
1566             <span class="s1">value = cache.get(lookup)</span>
1567             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">value </span><span class="s3">is </span><span class="s1">cache.not_in_cache:</span>
1568                 <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache_stats[MISS] += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1569                 <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1570                     <span class="s1">value = self._parseNoCache(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callPreParse)</span>
1571                 <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">pe:</span>
1572                     <span class="s0"># cache a copy of the exception, without the traceback</span>
1573                     <span class="s1">cache.set(lookup</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">pe.__class__(*pe.args))</span>
1574                     <span class="s3">raise</span>
1575                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1576                     <span class="s1">cache.set(lookup</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">(value[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">value[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">].copy()))</span>
1577                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">value</span>
1578             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1579                 <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache_stats[HIT] += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1580                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(value</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">Exception):</span>
1581                     <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">value</span>
1582                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">(value[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">value[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">].copy())</span>

1586     <span class="s1">@staticmethod</span>
1587     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">resetCache():</span>
1588         <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache.clear()</span>
1589         <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache_stats[:] = [</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] * len(ParserElement.packrat_cache_stats)</span>

1591     <span class="s1">_packratEnabled = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
1592     <span class="s1">@staticmethod</span>
1593     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">enablePackrat(cache_size_limit=</span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1594         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;Enables &quot;packrat&quot; parsing, which adds memoizing to the parsing logic. 
1595            Repeated parse attempts at the same string location (which happens 
1596            often in many complex grammars) can immediately return a cached value, 
1597            instead of re-executing parsing/validating code.  Memoizing is done of 
1598            both valid results and parsing exceptions. 
1599             
1600            Parameters: 
1601             - cache_size_limit - (default=C{128}) - if an integer value is provided 
1602               will limit the size of the packrat cache; if None is passed, then 
1603               the cache size will be unbounded; if 0 is passed, the cache will 
1604               be effectively disabled. 
1605              
1606            This speedup may break existing programs that use parse actions that 
1607            have side-effects.  For this reason, packrat parsing is disabled when 
1608            you first import pyparsing.  To activate the packrat feature, your 
1609            program must call the class method C{ParserElement.enablePackrat()}.  If 
1610            your program uses C{psyco} to &quot;compile as you go&quot;, you must call 
1611            C{enablePackrat} before calling C{psyco.full()}.  If you do not do this, 
1612            Python will crash.  For best results, call C{enablePackrat()} immediately 
1613            after importing pyparsing. 
1614             
1615            Example:: 
1616                import pyparsing 
1617                pyparsing.ParserElement.enablePackrat() 
1618         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1619         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">ParserElement._packratEnabled:</span>
1620             <span class="s1">ParserElement._packratEnabled = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
1621             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">cache_size_limit </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1622                 <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache = ParserElement._UnboundedCache()</span>
1623             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1624                 <span class="s1">ParserElement.packrat_cache = ParserElement._FifoCache(cache_size_limit)</span>
1625             <span class="s1">ParserElement._parse = ParserElement._parseCache</span>
1626 
1627     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseString( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">parseAll=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">):</span>
1628         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1629         Execute the parse expression with the given string. 
1630         This is the main interface to the client code, once the complete 
1631         expression has been built. 
1632  
1633         If you want the grammar to require that the entire input string be 
1634         successfully parsed, then set C{parseAll} to True (equivalent to ending 
1635         the grammar with C{L{StringEnd()}}). 
1636  
1637         Note: C{parseString} implicitly calls C{expandtabs()} on the input string, 
1638         in order to report proper column numbers in parse actions. 
1639         If the input string contains tabs and 
1640         the grammar uses parse actions that use the C{loc} argument to index into the 
1641         string being parsed, you can ensure you have a consistent view of the input 
1642         string by: 
1643          - calling C{parseWithTabs} on your grammar before calling C{parseString} 
1644            (see L{I{parseWithTabs}&lt;parseWithTabs&gt;}) 
1645          - define your parse action using the full C{(s,loc,toks)} signature, and 
1646            reference the input string using the parse action's C{s} argument 
1647          - explictly expand the tabs in your input string before calling 
1648            C{parseString} 
1649          
1650         Example:: 
1651             Word('a').parseString('aaaaabaaa')  # -&gt; ['aaaaa'] 
1652             Word('a').parseString('aaaaabaaa', parseAll=True)  # -&gt; Exception: Expected end of text 
1653         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1654         <span class="s1">ParserElement.resetCache()</span>
1655         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">self.streamlined:</span>
1656             <span class="s1">self.streamline()</span>
1657             <span class="s0">#~ self.saveAsList = True</span>
1658         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.ignoreExprs:</span>
1659             <span class="s1">e.streamline()</span>
1660         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">self.keepTabs:</span>
1661             <span class="s1">instring = instring.expandtabs()</span>
1662         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1663             <span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tokens = self._parse( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s1">)</span>
1664             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">parseAll:</span>
1665                 <span class="s1">loc = self.preParse( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc )</span>
1666                 <span class="s1">se = Empty() + StringEnd()</span>
1667                 <span class="s1">se._parse( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc )</span>
1668         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
1669             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ParserElement.verbose_stacktrace:</span>
1670                 <span class="s3">raise</span>
1671             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1672                 <span class="s0"># catch and re-raise exception from here, clears out pyparsing internal stack trace</span>
1673                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">exc</span>
1674         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1675             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">tokens</span>
