1677     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">scanString( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxMatches=_MAX_INT</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">overlap=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">):</span>
1678         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1679         Scan the input string for expression matches.  Each match will return the 
1680         matching tokens, start location, and end location.  May be called with optional 
1681         C{maxMatches} argument, to clip scanning after 'n' matches are found.  If 
1682         C{overlap} is specified, then overlapping matches will be reported. 
1683  
1684         Note that the start and end locations are reported relative to the string 
1685         being parsed.  See L{I{parseString}&lt;parseString&gt;} for more information on parsing 
1686         strings with embedded tabs. 
1687  
1688         Example:: 
1689             source = &quot;sldjf123lsdjjkf345sldkjf879lkjsfd987&quot; 
1690             print(source) 
1691             for tokens,start,end in Word(alphas).scanString(source): 
1692                 print(' '*start + '^'*(end-start)) 
1693                 print(' '*start + tokens[0]) 
1694          
1695         prints:: 
1696          
1697             sldjf123lsdjjkf345sldkjf879lkjsfd987 
1698             ^^^^^ 
1699             sldjf 
1700                     ^^^^^^^ 
1701                     lsdjjkf 
1702                               ^^^^^^ 
1703                               sldkjf 
1704                                        ^^^^^^ 
1705                                        lkjsfd 
1706         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1707         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">self.streamlined:</span>
1708             <span class="s1">self.streamline()</span>
1709         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.ignoreExprs:</span>
1710             <span class="s1">e.streamline()</span>
1711 
1712         <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">self.keepTabs:</span>
1713             <span class="s1">instring = _ustr(instring).expandtabs()</span>
1714         <span class="s1">instrlen = len(instring)</span>
1715         <span class="s1">loc = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
1716         <span class="s1">preparseFn = self.preParse</span>
1717         <span class="s1">parseFn = self._parse</span>
1718         <span class="s1">ParserElement.resetCache()</span>
1719         <span class="s1">matches = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
1720         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1721             <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s1">loc &lt;= instrlen </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">matches &lt; maxMatches:</span>
1722                 <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1723                     <span class="s1">preloc = preparseFn( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc )</span>
1724                     <span class="s1">nextLoc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">tokens = parseFn( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">preloc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callPreParse=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">)</span>
1725                 <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseException:</span>
1726                     <span class="s1">loc = preloc+</span><span class="s4">1</span>
1727                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1728                     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">nextLoc &gt; loc:</span>
1729                         <span class="s1">matches += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1730                         <span class="s3">yield </span><span class="s1">tokens</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">preloc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">nextLoc</span>
1731                         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">overlap:</span>
1732                             <span class="s1">nextloc = preparseFn( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc )</span>
1733                             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">nextloc &gt; loc:</span>
1734                                 <span class="s1">loc = nextLoc</span>
1735                             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1736                                 <span class="s1">loc += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
1737                         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1738                             <span class="s1">loc = nextLoc</span>
1739                     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1740                         <span class="s1">loc = preloc+</span><span class="s4">1</span>
1741         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
1742             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ParserElement.verbose_stacktrace:</span>
1743                 <span class="s3">raise</span>
1744             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1745                 <span class="s0"># catch and re-raise exception from here, clears out pyparsing internal stack trace</span>
1746                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">exc</span>

1748     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">transformString( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring ):</span>
1749         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1750         Extension to C{L{scanString}}, to modify matching text with modified tokens that may 
1751         be returned from a parse action.  To use C{transformString}, define a grammar and 
1752         attach a parse action to it that modifies the returned token list. 
1753         Invoking C{transformString()} on a target string will then scan for matches, 
1754         and replace the matched text patterns according to the logic in the parse 
1755         action.  C{transformString()} returns the resulting transformed string. 
1756          
1757         Example:: 
1758             wd = Word(alphas) 
1759             wd.setParseAction(lambda toks: toks[0].title()) 
1760              
1761             print(wd.transformString(&quot;now is the winter of our discontent made glorious summer by this sun of york.&quot;)) 
1762         Prints:: 
1763             Now Is The Winter Of Our Discontent Made Glorious Summer By This Sun Of York. 
1764         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1765         <span class="s1">out = []</span>
1766         <span class="s1">lastE = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
1767         <span class="s0"># force preservation of &lt;TAB&gt;s, to minimize unwanted transformation of string, and to</span>
1768         <span class="s0"># keep string locs straight between transformString and scanString</span>
1769         <span class="s1">self.keepTabs = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
1770         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1771             <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">t</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.scanString( instring ):</span>
1772                 <span class="s1">out.append( instring[lastE:s] )</span>
1773                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">t:</span>
1774                     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(t</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
1775                         <span class="s1">out += t.asList()</span>
1776                     <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">isinstance(t</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">list):</span>
1777                         <span class="s1">out += t</span>
1778                     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1779                         <span class="s1">out.append(t)</span>
1780                 <span class="s1">lastE = e</span>
1781             <span class="s1">out.append(instring[lastE:])</span>
1782             <span class="s1">out = [o </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">o </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">out </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">o]</span>
1783             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(map(_ustr</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">_flatten(out)))</span>
1784         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
1785             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ParserElement.verbose_stacktrace:</span>
1786                 <span class="s3">raise</span>
1787             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1788                 <span class="s0"># catch and re-raise exception from here, clears out pyparsing internal stack trace</span>
1789                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">exc</span>
1790 
1791     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">searchString( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxMatches=_MAX_INT ):</span>
1792         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1793         Another extension to C{L{scanString}}, simplifying the access to the tokens found 
1794         to match the given parse expression.  May be called with optional 
1795         C{maxMatches} argument, to clip searching after 'n' matches are found. 
1796          
1797         Example:: 
1798             # a capitalized word starts with an uppercase letter, followed by zero or more lowercase letters 
1799             cap_word = Word(alphas.upper(), alphas.lower()) 
1800              
1801             print(cap_word.searchString(&quot;More than Iron, more than Lead, more than Gold I need Electricity&quot;)) 
1802  
1803             # the sum() builtin can be used to merge results into a single ParseResults object 
1804             print(sum(cap_word.searchString(&quot;More than Iron, more than Lead, more than Gold I need Electricity&quot;))) 
1805         prints:: 
1806             [['More'], ['Iron'], ['Lead'], ['Gold'], ['I'], ['Electricity']] 
1807             ['More', 'Iron', 'Lead', 'Gold', 'I', 'Electricity'] 
1808         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1809         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1810             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ParseResults([ t </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">t</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.scanString( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxMatches ) ])</span>
1811         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
1812             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ParserElement.verbose_stacktrace:</span>
1813                 <span class="s3">raise</span>
1814             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1815                 <span class="s0"># catch and re-raise exception from here, clears out pyparsing internal stack trace</span>
1816                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">exc</span>

1818     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">split(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxsplit=_MAX_INT</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">includeSeparators=</span><span class="s3">False</span><span class="s1">):</span>
1819         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1820         Generator method to split a string using the given expression as a separator. 
1821         May be called with optional C{maxsplit} argument, to limit the number of splits; 
1822         and the optional C{includeSeparators} argument (default=C{False}), if the separating 
1823         matching text should be included in the split results. 
1824          
1825         Example::         
1826             punc = oneOf(list(&quot;.,;:/-!?&quot;)) 
1827             print(list(punc.split(&quot;This, this?, this sentence, is badly punctuated!&quot;))) 
1828         prints:: 
1829             ['This', ' this', '', ' this sentence', ' is badly punctuated', ''] 
1830         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1831         <span class="s1">splits = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
1832         <span class="s1">last = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
1833         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">t</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.scanString(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxMatches=maxsplit):</span>
1834             <span class="s3">yield </span><span class="s1">instring[last:s]</span>
1835             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">includeSeparators:</span>
1836                 <span class="s3">yield </span><span class="s1">t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1837             <span class="s1">last = e</span>
1838         <span class="s3">yield </span><span class="s1">instring[last:]</span>

1840     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__add__(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other ):</span>

1843         converts them to L{Literal}s by default.

1846             greet = Word(alphas) + &quot;,&quot; + Word(alphas) + &quot;!&quot;

1849         Prints:: 
1850             Hello, World! -&gt; ['Hello', ',', 'World', '!'] 
1851         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

1896     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__mul__(self</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">other):</span>
1897         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
1898         Implementation of * operator, allows use of C{expr * 3} in place of 
1899         C{expr + expr + expr}.  Expressions may also me multiplied by a 2-integer 
1900         tuple, similar to C{{min,max}} multipliers in regular expressions.  Tuples 
1901         may also include C{None} as in: 
1902          - C{expr*(n,None)} or C{expr*(n,)} is equivalent 
1903               to C{expr*n + L{ZeroOrMore}(expr)} 
1904               (read as &quot;at least n instances of C{expr}&quot;) 
1905          - C{expr*(None,n)} is equivalent to C{expr*(0,n)} 
1906               (read as &quot;0 to n instances of C{expr}&quot;) 
1907          - C{expr*(None,None)} is equivalent to C{L{ZeroOrMore}(expr)} 
1908          - C{expr*(1,None)} is equivalent to C{L{OneOrMore}(expr)} 
1909  
1910         Note that C{expr*(None,n)} does not raise an exception if 
1911         more than n exprs exist in the input stream; that is, 
1912         C{expr*(None,n)} does not enforce a maximum number of expr 
1913         occurrences.  If this behavior is desired, then write 
1914         C{expr*(None,n) + ~expr} 
1915         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
1916         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int):</span>
1917             <span class="s1">minElements</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">optElements = other</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s4">0</span>
1918         <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">tuple):</span>
1919             <span class="s1">other = (other + (</span><span class="s3">None, None</span><span class="s1">))[:</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">]</span>
1920             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1921                 <span class="s1">other = (</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">])</span>
1922             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">other[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1923                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] == </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1924                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ZeroOrMore(self)</span>
1925                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1926                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">OneOrMore(self)</span>
1927                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1928                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self*other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">] + ZeroOrMore(self)</span>
1929             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">isinstance(other[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int):</span>
1930                 <span class="s1">minElements</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">optElements = other</span>
1931                 <span class="s1">optElements -= minElements</span>
1932             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1933                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">TypeError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;cannot multiply 'ParserElement' and ('%s','%s') objects&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">type(other[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">])</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">type(other[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]))</span>
1934         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1935             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">TypeError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;cannot multiply 'ParserElement' and '%s' objects&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">type(other))</span>
1936 
1937         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">minElements &lt; </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1938             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;cannot multiply ParserElement by negative value&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
1939         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">optElements &lt; </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1940             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;second tuple value must be greater or equal to first tuple value&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
1941         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">minElements == optElements == </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1942             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;cannot multiply ParserElement by 0 or (0,0)&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
1943 
1944         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(optElements):</span>
1945             <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">makeOptionalList(n):</span>
1946                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">n&gt;</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1947                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Optional(self + makeOptionalList(n-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
1948                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1949                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Optional(self)</span>
1950             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">minElements:</span>
1951                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">minElements == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1952                     <span class="s1">ret = self + makeOptionalList(optElements)</span>
1953                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1954                     <span class="s1">ret = And([self]*minElements) + makeOptionalList(optElements)</span>
1955             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1956                 <span class="s1">ret = makeOptionalList(optElements)</span>
1957         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1958             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">minElements == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1959                 <span class="s1">ret = self</span>
1960             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
1961                 <span class="s1">ret = And([self]*minElements)</span>
1962         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>

2045     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__call__(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">name=</span><span class="s3">None</span><span class="s1">):</span>

2098     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">ignore( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other ):</span>
2099         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;

2113

2119         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self</span>

2131     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">setDebug( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">flag=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2132         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2133         Enable display of debugging messages while doing pattern matching. 
2134         Set C{flag} to True to enable, False to disable. 
2135  
2136         Example:: 
2137             wd = Word(alphas).setName(&quot;alphaword&quot;) 
2138             integer = Word(nums).setName(&quot;numword&quot;) 
2139             term = wd | integer 
2140

2142             wd.setDebug()

2148             Matched alphaword -&gt; ['abc'] 
2149             Match alphaword at loc 3(1,4) 
2150             Exception raised:Expected alphaword (at char 4), (line:1, col:5) 
2151             Match alphaword at loc 7(1,8) 
2152             Matched alphaword -&gt; ['xyz'] 
2153             Match alphaword at loc 11(1,12)

2155             Match alphaword at loc 15(1,16) 
2156             Exception raised:Expected alphaword (at char 15), (line:1, col:16) 
2157  
2158         The output shown is that produced by the default debug actions - custom debug actions can be 
2159         specified using L{setDebugActions}. Prior to attempting 
2160         to match the C{wd} expression, the debugging message C{&quot;Match &lt;exprname&gt; at loc &lt;n&gt;(&lt;line&gt;,&lt;col&gt;)&quot;} 
2161         is shown. Then if the parse succeeds, a C{&quot;Matched&quot;} message is shown, or an C{&quot;Exception raised&quot;} 
2162         message is shown. Also note the use of L{setName} to assign a human-readable name to the expression, 
2163         which makes debugging and exception messages easier to understand - for instance, the default 
2164         name created for the C{Word} expression without calling C{setName} is C{&quot;W:(ABCD...)&quot;}. 
2165         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2166         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">flag:</span>

2232     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">matches(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">testString</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">parseAll=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>
2233         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2234         Method for quick testing of a parser against a test string. Good for simple  
2235         inline microtests of sub expressions while building up larger parser. 
2236             
2237         Parameters: 
2238          - testString - to test against this expression for a match 
2239          - parseAll - (default=C{True}) - flag to pass to C{L{parseString}} when running tests 
2240              
2241         Example:: 
2242             expr = Word(nums) 
2243             assert expr.matches(&quot;100&quot;) 
2244         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2245         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2246             <span class="s1">self.parseString(_ustr(testString)</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">parseAll=parseAll)</span>
2247             <span class="s3">return True</span>
2248         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException:</span>
2249             <span class="s3">return False</span>
2250                 
2251     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">runTests(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tests</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">parseAll=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">comment=</span><span class="s2">'#'</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">fullDump=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">printResults=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">failureTests=</span><span class="s3">False</span><span class="s1">):</span>
2252         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2253         Execute the parse expression on a series of test strings, showing each 
2254         test, the parsed results or where the parse failed. Quick and easy way to 
2255         run a parse expression against a list of sample strings. 
2256             
2257         Parameters: 
2258          - tests - a list of separate test strings, or a multiline string of test strings 
2259          - parseAll - (default=C{True}) - flag to pass to C{L{parseString}} when running tests            
2260          - comment - (default=C{'#'}) - expression for indicating embedded comments in the test  
2261               string; pass None to disable comment filtering 
2262          - fullDump - (default=C{True}) - dump results as list followed by results names in nested outline; 
2263               if False, only dump nested list 
2264          - printResults - (default=C{True}) prints test output to stdout 
2265          - failureTests - (default=C{False}) indicates if these tests are expected to fail parsing 
2266  
2267         Returns: a (success, results) tuple, where success indicates that all tests succeeded 
2268         (or failed if C{failureTests} is True), and the results contain a list of lines of each  
2269         test's output 
2270          
2271         Example:: 
2272             number_expr = pyparsing_common.number.copy() 
2273  
2274             result = number_expr.runTests(''' 
2275                 # unsigned integer 
2276                 100 
2277                 # negative integer 
2278                 -100 
2279                 # float with scientific notation 
2280                 6.02e23 
2281                 # integer with scientific notation 
2282                 1e-12 
2283                 ''') 
2284             print(&quot;Success&quot; if result[0] else &quot;Failed!&quot;) 
2285  
2286             result = number_expr.runTests(''' 
2287                 # stray character 
2288                 100Z 
2289                 # missing leading digit before '.' 
2290                 -.100 
2291                 # too many '.' 
2292                 3.14.159 
2293                 ''', failureTests=True) 
2294             print(&quot;Success&quot; if result[0] else &quot;Failed!&quot;) 
2295         prints:: 
2296             # unsigned integer 
2297             100 
2298             [100] 
2299  
2300             # negative integer 
2301             -100 
2302             [-100] 
2303  
2304             # float with scientific notation 
2305             6.02e23 
2306             [6.02e+23] 
2307  
2308             # integer with scientific notation 
2309             1e-12 
2310             [1e-12] 
2311  
2312             Success 
2313              
2314             # stray character 
2315             100Z 
2316                ^ 
2317             FAIL: Expected end of text (at char 3), (line:1, col:4) 
2318  
2319             # missing leading digit before '.' 
2320             -.100 
2321             ^ 
2322             FAIL: Expected {real number with scientific notation | real number | signed integer} (at char 0), (line:1, col:1) 
2323  
2324             # too many '.' 
2325             3.14.159 
2326                 ^ 
2327             FAIL: Expected end of text (at char 4), (line:1, col:5) 
2328  
2329             Success 
2330  
2331         Each test string must be on a single line. If you want to test a string that spans multiple 
2332         lines, create a test like this:: 
2333  
2334             expr.runTest(r&quot;this is a test\\n of strings that spans \\n 3 lines&quot;) 
2335          
2336         (Note that this is a raw string literal, you must include the leading 'r'.) 
2337         &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2338         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(tests</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">basestring):</span>
2339             <span class="s1">tests = list(map(str.strip</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tests.rstrip().splitlines()))</span>
2340         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(comment</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">basestring):</span>
2341             <span class="s1">comment = Literal(comment)</span>
2342         <span class="s1">allResults = []</span>
2343         <span class="s1">comments = []</span>
2344         <span class="s1">success = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
2345         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">t </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tests:</span>
2346             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">comment </span><span class="s3">is not None and </span><span class="s1">comment.matches(t</span><span class="s3">, False</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">comments </span><span class="s3">and not </span><span class="s1">t:</span>
2347                 <span class="s1">comments.append(t)</span>
2348                 <span class="s3">continue</span>
2349             <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">t:</span>
2350                 <span class="s3">continue</span>
2351             <span class="s1">out = [</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s1">.join(comments)</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">t]</span>
2352             <span class="s1">comments = []</span>
2353             <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2354                 <span class="s1">t = t.replace(</span><span class="s2">r'\n'</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s1">)</span>
2355                 <span class="s1">result = self.parseString(t</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">parseAll=parseAll)</span>
2356                 <span class="s1">out.append(result.dump(full=fullDump))</span>
2357                 <span class="s1">success = success </span><span class="s3">and not </span><span class="s1">failureTests</span>
2358             <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">pe:</span>
2359                 <span class="s1">fatal = </span><span class="s2">&quot;(FATAL)&quot; </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(pe</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">ParseFatalException) </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>
2360                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">' </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">t:</span>
2361                     <span class="s1">out.append(line(pe.loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">t))</span>
2362                     <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">' '</span><span class="s1">*(col(pe.loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t)-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">) + </span><span class="s2">'^' </span><span class="s1">+ fatal)</span>
2363                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2364                     <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">' '</span><span class="s1">*pe.loc + </span><span class="s2">'^' </span><span class="s1">+ fatal)</span>
2365                 <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">&quot;FAIL: &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ str(pe))</span>
2366                 <span class="s1">success = success </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">failureTests</span>
2367                 <span class="s1">result = pe</span>
2368             <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">Exception </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
2369                 <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">&quot;FAIL-EXCEPTION: &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ str(exc))</span>
2370                 <span class="s1">success = success </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">failureTests</span>
2371                 <span class="s1">result = exc</span>
2372 
2373             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">printResults:</span>
2374                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">fullDump:</span>
2375                     <span class="s1">out.append(</span><span class="s2">''</span><span class="s1">)</span>
2376                 <span class="s1">print(</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s1">.join(out))</span>
2377 
2378             <span class="s1">allResults.append((t</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">result))</span>
2379         
2380         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">success</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">allResults</span>
2381 
2382

2417 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Literal(Token):</span>
2418     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2419     Token to exactly match a specified string. 
2420      
2421     Example:: 
2422         Literal('blah').parseString('blah')  # -&gt; ['blah'] 
2423         Literal('blah').parseString('blahfooblah')  # -&gt; ['blah'] 
2424         Literal('blah').parseString('bla')  # -&gt; Exception: Expected &quot;blah&quot; 
2425      
2426     For case-insensitive matching, use L{CaselessLiteral}. 
2427      
2428     For keyword matching (force word break before and after the matched string), 
2429     use L{Keyword} or L{CaselessKeyword}. 
2430     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2431     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">matchString ):</span>
2432         <span class="s1">super(Literal</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
2433         <span class="s1">self.match = matchString</span>
2434         <span class="s1">self.matchLen = len(matchString)</span>
2435         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2436             <span class="s1">self.firstMatchChar = matchString[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
2437         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">IndexError:</span>
2438             <span class="s1">warnings.warn(</span><span class="s2">&quot;null string passed to Literal; use Empty() instead&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
2439                             <span class="s1">SyntaxWarning</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">stacklevel=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
2440             <span class="s1">self.__class__ = Empty</span>
2441         <span class="s1">self.name = </span><span class="s2">'&quot;%s&quot;' </span><span class="s1">% _ustr(self.match)</span>
2442         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ self.name</span>
2443         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2444         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2445 
2446     <span class="s0"># Performance tuning: this routine gets called a *lot*</span>
2447     <span class="s0"># if this is a single character match string  and the first character matches,</span>
2448     <span class="s0"># short-circuit as quickly as possible, and avoid calling startswith</span>
2449     <span class="s0">#~ @profile</span>
2450     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2451         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(instring[loc] == self.firstMatchChar </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2452             <span class="s1">(self.matchLen==</span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring.startswith(self.match</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc)) ):</span>
2453             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc+self.matchLen</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.match</span>
2454         <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>
2455 <span class="s1">_L = Literal</span>
2456 <span class="s1">ParserElement._literalStringClass = Literal</span>

2458 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Keyword(Token):</span>
2459     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2460     Token to exactly match a specified string as a keyword, that is, it must be 
2461     immediately followed by a non-keyword character.  Compare with C{L{Literal}}: 
2462      - C{Literal(&quot;if&quot;)} will match the leading C{'if'} in C{'ifAndOnlyIf'}. 
2463      - C{Keyword(&quot;if&quot;)} will not; it will only match the leading C{'if'} in C{'if x=1'}, or C{'if(y==2)'} 
2464     Accepts two optional constructor arguments in addition to the keyword string: 
2465      - C{identChars} is a string of characters that would be valid identifier characters, 
2466           defaulting to all alphanumerics + &quot;_&quot; and &quot;$&quot; 
2467      - C{caseless} allows case-insensitive matching, default is C{False}. 
2468         
2469     Example:: 
2470         Keyword(&quot;start&quot;).parseString(&quot;start&quot;)  # -&gt; ['start'] 
2471         Keyword(&quot;start&quot;).parseString(&quot;starting&quot;)  # -&gt; Exception 
2472  
2473     For case-insensitive matching, use L{CaselessKeyword}. 
2474     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2475     <span class="s1">DEFAULT_KEYWORD_CHARS = alphanums+</span><span class="s2">&quot;_$&quot;</span>
2476 
2477     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">matchString</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">identChars=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">caseless=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2478         <span class="s1">super(Keyword</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
2479         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">identChars </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2480             <span class="s1">identChars = Keyword.DEFAULT_KEYWORD_CHARS</span>
2481         <span class="s1">self.match = matchString</span>
2482         <span class="s1">self.matchLen = len(matchString)</span>
2483         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2484             <span class="s1">self.firstMatchChar = matchString[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
2485         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">IndexError:</span>
2486             <span class="s1">warnings.warn(</span><span class="s2">&quot;null string passed to Keyword; use Empty() instead&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
2487                             <span class="s1">SyntaxWarning</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">stacklevel=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
2488         <span class="s1">self.name = </span><span class="s2">'&quot;%s&quot;' </span><span class="s1">% self.match</span>
2489         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ self.name</span>
2490         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2491         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2492         <span class="s1">self.caseless = caseless</span>
2493         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">caseless:</span>
2494             <span class="s1">self.caselessmatch = matchString.upper()</span>
2495             <span class="s1">identChars = identChars.upper()</span>
2496         <span class="s1">self.identChars = set(identChars)</span>
2497 
2498     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2499         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.caseless:</span>
2500             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">( (instring[ loc:loc+self.matchLen ].upper() == self.caselessmatch) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2501                  <span class="s1">(loc &gt;= len(instring)-self.matchLen </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring[loc+self.matchLen].upper() </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.identChars) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2502                  <span class="s1">(loc == </span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring[loc-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">].upper() </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.identChars) ):</span>
2503                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc+self.matchLen</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.match</span>
2504         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2505             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(instring[loc] == self.firstMatchChar </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2506                 <span class="s1">(self.matchLen==</span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring.startswith(self.match</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc)) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2507                 <span class="s1">(loc &gt;= len(instring)-self.matchLen </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring[loc+self.matchLen] </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.identChars) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
2508                 <span class="s1">(loc == </span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">instring[loc-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.identChars) ):</span>
2509                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc+self.matchLen</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.match</span>
2510         <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>

2514         <span class="s1">c.identChars = Keyword.DEFAULT_KEYWORD_CHARS</span>
2515         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">c</span>

2523 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">CaselessLiteral(Literal):</span>
2524     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2525     Token to match a specified string, ignoring case of letters. 
2526     Note: the matched results will always be in the case of the given 
2527     match string, NOT the case of the input text. 
2528  
2529     Example:: 
2530         OneOrMore(CaselessLiteral(&quot;CMD&quot;)).parseString(&quot;cmd CMD Cmd10&quot;) # -&gt; ['CMD', 'CMD', 'CMD'] 
2531          
2532     (Contrast with example for L{CaselessKeyword}.) 
2533     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2534     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">matchString ):</span>
2535         <span class="s1">super(CaselessLiteral</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__( matchString.upper() )</span>
2536         <span class="s0"># Preserve the defining literal.</span>
2537         <span class="s1">self.returnString = matchString</span>
2538         <span class="s1">self.name = </span><span class="s2">&quot;'%s'&quot; </span><span class="s1">% self.returnString</span>
2539         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ self.name</span>
2540 
2541     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2542         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">instring[ loc:loc+self.matchLen ].upper() == self.match:</span>
2543             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc+self.matchLen</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.returnString</span>
2544         <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>

2564 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">CloseMatch(Token):</span>
2565     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2566     A variation on L{Literal} which matches &quot;close&quot; matches, that is,  
2567     strings with at most 'n' mismatching characters. C{CloseMatch} takes parameters: 
2568      - C{match_string} - string to be matched 
2569      - C{maxMismatches} - (C{default=1}) maximum number of mismatches allowed to count as a match 
2570      
2571     The results from a successful parse will contain the matched text from the input string and the following named results: 
2572      - C{mismatches} - a list of the positions within the match_string where mismatches were found 
2573      - C{original} - the original match_string used to compare against the input string 
2574      
2575     If C{mismatches} is an empty list, then the match was an exact match. 
2576      
2577     Example:: 
2578         patt = CloseMatch(&quot;ATCATCGAATGGA&quot;) 
2579         patt.parseString(&quot;ATCATCGAAXGGA&quot;) # -&gt; (['ATCATCGAAXGGA'], {'mismatches': [[9]], 'original': ['ATCATCGAATGGA']}) 
2580         patt.parseString(&quot;ATCAXCGAAXGGA&quot;) # -&gt; Exception: Expected 'ATCATCGAATGGA' (with up to 1 mismatches) (at char 0), (line:1, col:1) 
2581  
2582         # exact match 
2583         patt.parseString(&quot;ATCATCGAATGGA&quot;) # -&gt; (['ATCATCGAATGGA'], {'mismatches': [[]], 'original': ['ATCATCGAATGGA']}) 
2584  
2585         # close match allowing up to 2 mismatches 
2586         patt = CloseMatch(&quot;ATCATCGAATGGA&quot;, maxMismatches=2) 
2587         patt.parseString(&quot;ATCAXCGAAXGGA&quot;) # -&gt; (['ATCAXCGAAXGGA'], {'mismatches': [[4, 9]], 'original': ['ATCATCGAATGGA']}) 
2588     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2589     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">match_string</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">maxMismatches=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">):</span>
2590         <span class="s1">super(CloseMatch</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
2591         <span class="s1">self.name = match_string</span>
2592         <span class="s1">self.match_string = match_string</span>
2593         <span class="s1">self.maxMismatches = maxMismatches</span>
2594         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected %r (with up to %d mismatches)&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (self.match_string</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.maxMismatches)</span>
2595         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2596         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
2597 
2598     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2599         <span class="s1">start = loc</span>
2600         <span class="s1">instrlen = len(instring)</span>
2601         <span class="s1">maxloc = start + len(self.match_string)</span>
2602 
2603         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">maxloc &lt;= instrlen:</span>
2604             <span class="s1">match_string = self.match_string</span>
2605             <span class="s1">match_stringloc = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
2606             <span class="s1">mismatches = []</span>
2607             <span class="s1">maxMismatches = self.maxMismatches</span>
2608 
2609             <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">match_stringloc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s_m </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(zip(instring[loc:maxloc]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.match_string)):</span>
2610                 <span class="s1">src</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">mat = s_m</span>
2611                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">src != mat:</span>
2612                     <span class="s1">mismatches.append(match_stringloc)</span>
2613                     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(mismatches) &gt; maxMismatches:</span>
2614                         <span class="s3">break</span>
2615             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
2616                 <span class="s1">loc = match_stringloc + </span><span class="s4">1</span>
2617                 <span class="s1">results = ParseResults([instring[start:loc]])</span>
2618                 <span class="s1">results[</span><span class="s2">'original'</span><span class="s1">] = self.match_string</span>
2619                 <span class="s1">results[</span><span class="s2">'mismatches'</span><span class="s1">] = mismatches</span>
2620                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">results</span>
2621 
2622         <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>

2624 
2625 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Word(Token):</span>
2626     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2627     Token for matching words composed of allowed character sets. 
2628     Defined with string containing all allowed initial characters, 
2629     an optional string containing allowed body characters (if omitted, 
2630     defaults to the initial character set), and an optional minimum, 
2631     maximum, and/or exact length.  The default value for C{min} is 1 (a 
2632     minimum value &lt; 1 is not valid); the default values for C{max} and C{exact} 
2633     are 0, meaning no maximum or exact length restriction. An optional 
2634     C{excludeChars} parameter can list characters that might be found in  
2635     the input C{bodyChars} string; useful to define a word of all printables 
2636     except for one or two characters, for instance. 
2637      
2638     L{srange} is useful for defining custom character set strings for defining  
2639     C{Word} expressions, using range notation from regular expression character sets. 
2640      
2641     A common mistake is to use C{Word} to match a specific literal string, as in  
2642     C{Word(&quot;Address&quot;)}. Remember that C{Word} uses the string argument to define 
2643     I{sets} of matchable characters. This expression would match &quot;Add&quot;, &quot;AAA&quot;, 
2644     &quot;dAred&quot;, or any other word made up of the characters 'A', 'd', 'r', 'e', and 's'. 
2645     To match an exact literal string, use L{Literal} or L{Keyword}. 
2646  
2647     pyparsing includes helper strings for building Words: 
2648      - L{alphas} 
2649      - L{nums} 
2650      - L{alphanums} 
2651      - L{hexnums} 
2652      - L{alphas8bit} (alphabetic characters in ASCII range 128-255 - accented, tilded, umlauted, etc.) 
2653      - L{punc8bit} (non-alphabetic characters in ASCII range 128-255 - currency, symbols, superscripts, diacriticals, etc.) 
2654      - L{printables} (any non-whitespace character) 
2655  
2656     Example:: 
2657         # a word composed of digits 
2658         integer = Word(nums) # equivalent to Word(&quot;0123456789&quot;) or Word(srange(&quot;0-9&quot;)) 
2659          
2660         # a word with a leading capital, and zero or more lowercase 
2661         capital_word = Word(alphas.upper(), alphas.lower()) 
2662  
2663         # hostnames are alphanumeric, with leading alpha, and '-' 
2664         hostname = Word(alphas, alphanums+'-') 
2665          
2666         # roman numeral (not a strict parser, accepts invalid mix of characters) 
2667         roman = Word(&quot;IVXLCDM&quot;) 
2668          
2669         # any string of non-whitespace characters, except for ',' 
2670         csv_value = Word(printables, excludeChars=&quot;,&quot;) 
2671     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2672     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">initChars</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">bodyChars=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">min=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">max=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">asKeyword=</span><span class="s3">False, </span><span class="s1">excludeChars=</span><span class="s3">None </span><span class="s1">):</span>

2687         <span class="s1">self.maxSpecified = max &gt; </span><span class="s4">0</span>

2706         <span class="s1">self.asKeyword = asKeyword</span>

2708         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s2">' ' </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.initCharsOrig+self.bodyCharsOrig </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">(min==</span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">max==</span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">exact==</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">):</span>

2727         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.re:</span>

2738         <span class="s1">start = loc</span>
2739         <span class="s1">loc += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
2740         <span class="s1">instrlen = len(instring)</span>
2741         <span class="s1">bodychars = self.bodyChars</span>
2742         <span class="s1">maxloc = start + self.maxLen</span>

2753             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">(start&gt;</span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">instring[start-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">bodychars) </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">(loc&lt;instrlen </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">instring[loc] </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">bodychars):</span>
2754                 <span class="s1">throwException = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
2755 
2756         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">throwException:</span>
2757             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>

2784 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Regex(Token):</span>
2785     <span class="s5">r&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2786     Token for matching strings that match a given regular expression. 
2787     Defined with string specifying the regular expression in a form recognized by the inbuilt Python re module. 
2788     If the given regex contains named groups (defined using C{(?P&lt;name&gt;...)}), these will be preserved as  
2789     named parse results. 
2790  
2791     Example:: 
2792         realnum = Regex(r&quot;[+-]?\d+\.\d*&quot;) 
2793         date = Regex(r'(?P&lt;year&gt;\d{4})-(?P&lt;month&gt;\d\d?)-(?P&lt;day&gt;\d\d?)') 
2794         # ref: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/267399/how-do-you-match-only-valid-roman-numerals-with-a-regular-expression 
2795         roman = Regex(r&quot;M{0,4}(CM|CD|D?C{0,3})(XC|XL|L?X{0,3})(IX|IV|V?I{0,3})&quot;) 
2796     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2797     <span class="s1">compiledREtype = type(re.compile(</span><span class="s2">&quot;[A-Z]&quot;</span><span class="s1">))</span>

2799         <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot;The parameters C{pattern} and C{flags} are passed to the C{re.compile()} function as-is. See the Python C{re} module for an explanation of the acceptable patterns and flags.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

2832     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>

2856 
2857 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">QuotedString(Token):</span>
2858     <span class="s5">r&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2859     Token for matching strings that are delimited by quoting characters. 
2860      
2861     Defined with the following parameters: 
2862         - quoteChar - string of one or more characters defining the quote delimiting string 
2863         - escChar - character to escape quotes, typically backslash (default=C{None}) 
2864         - escQuote - special quote sequence to escape an embedded quote string (such as SQL's &quot;&quot; to escape an embedded &quot;) (default=C{None}) 
2865         - multiline - boolean indicating whether quotes can span multiple lines (default=C{False}) 
2866         - unquoteResults - boolean indicating whether the matched text should be unquoted (default=C{True}) 
2867         - endQuoteChar - string of one or more characters defining the end of the quote delimited string (default=C{None} =&gt; same as quoteChar) 
2868         - convertWhitespaceEscapes - convert escaped whitespace (C{'\t'}, C{'\n'}, etc.) to actual whitespace (default=C{True}) 
2869  
2870     Example:: 
2871         qs = QuotedString('&quot;') 
2872         print(qs.searchString('lsjdf &quot;This is the quote&quot; sldjf')) 
2873         complex_qs = QuotedString('{{', endQuoteChar='}}') 
2874         print(complex_qs.searchString('lsjdf {{This is the &quot;quote&quot;}} sldjf')) 
2875         sql_qs = QuotedString('&quot;', escQuote='&quot;&quot;') 
2876         print(sql_qs.searchString('lsjdf &quot;This is the quote with &quot;&quot;embedded&quot;&quot; quotes&quot; sldjf')) 
2877     prints:: 
2878         [['This is the quote']] 
2879         [['This is the &quot;quote&quot;']] 
2880         [['This is the quote with &quot;embedded&quot; quotes']] 
2881     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
2882     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">quoteChar</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">escChar=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">escQuote=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">multiline=</span><span class="s3">False, </span><span class="s1">unquoteResults=</span><span class="s3">True, </span><span class="s1">endQuoteChar=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">convertWhitespaceEscapes=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>
2883         <span class="s1">super(QuotedString</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
2884 
2885         <span class="s0"># remove white space from quote chars - wont work anyway</span>
2886         <span class="s1">quoteChar = quoteChar.strip()</span>

2947     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
2948         <span class="s1">result = instring[loc] == self.firstQuoteChar </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">self.re.match(instring</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc) </span><span class="s3">or None</span>

2966                         <span class="s2">r'\f' </span><span class="s1">: </span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\f</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">,</span>
2967                         <span class="s2">r'\r' </span><span class="s1">: </span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">\r</span><span class="s2">'</span><span class="s3">,</span>

2994 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">CharsNotIn(Token):</span>
2995     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
2996     Token for matching words composed of characters I{not} in a given set (will 
2997     include whitespace in matched characters if not listed in the provided exclusion set - see example). 
2998     Defined with string containing all disallowed characters, and an optional 
2999     minimum, maximum, and/or exact length.  The default value for C{min} is 1 (a 
3000     minimum value &lt; 1 is not valid); the default values for C{max} and C{exact} 
3001     are 0, meaning no maximum or exact length restriction. 
3002  
3003     Example:: 
3004         # define a comma-separated-value as anything that is not a ',' 
3005         csv_value = CharsNotIn(',') 
3006         print(delimitedList(csv_value).parseString(&quot;dkls,lsdkjf,s12 34,@!#,213&quot;)) 
3007     prints:: 
3008         ['dkls', 'lsdkjf', 's12 34', '@!#', '213'] 
3009     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
3010     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">notChars</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">min=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">max=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3011         <span class="s1">super(CharsNotIn</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
3012         <span class="s1">self.skipWhitespace = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
3013         <span class="s1">self.notChars = notChars</span>
3014 
3015         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">min &lt; </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3016             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;cannot specify a minimum length &lt; 1; use Optional(CharsNotIn()) if zero-length char group is permitted&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
3017 
3018         <span class="s1">self.minLen = min</span>
3019 
3020         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">max &gt; </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3021             <span class="s1">self.maxLen = max</span>
3022         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3023             <span class="s1">self.maxLen = _MAX_INT</span>
3024 
3025         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">exact &gt; </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3026             <span class="s1">self.maxLen = exact</span>
3027             <span class="s1">self.minLen = exact</span>

3031         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = ( self.minLen == </span><span class="s4">0 </span><span class="s1">)</span>
3032         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = </span><span class="s3">False</span>

3034     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3035         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">instring[loc] </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.notChars:</span>
3036             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>

3065 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">White(Token):</span>
3066     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3067     Special matching class for matching whitespace.  Normally, whitespace is ignored 
3068     by pyparsing grammars.  This class is included when some whitespace structures 
3069     are significant.  Define with a string containing the whitespace characters to be 
3070     matched; default is C{&quot; \\t\\r\\n&quot;}.  Also takes optional C{min}, C{max}, and C{exact} arguments, 
3071     as defined for the C{L{Word}} class.

3073     <span class="s1">whiteStrs = {</span>

3076         <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s1">: </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;LF&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
3077         <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\r</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s1">: </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;CR&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
3078         <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\f</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s1">: </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;FF&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
3079         <span class="s1">}</span>
3080     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__(self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">ws=</span><span class="s2">&quot; </span><span class="s3">\t\r\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">min=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">max=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">):</span>
3081         <span class="s1">super(White</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__()</span>
3082         <span class="s1">self.matchWhite = ws</span>
3083         <span class="s1">self.setWhitespaceChars( </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(c </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.whiteChars </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">self.matchWhite) )</span>

3087         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ self.name</span>

3092             <span class="s1">self.maxLen = max</span>
3093         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>

3100     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>

3102             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>
3103         <span class="s1">start = loc</span>

3126     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

3131     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">preParse( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc ):</span>
3132         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">col(loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">instring) != self.col:</span>
3133             <span class="s1">instrlen = len(instring)</span>

3136             <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s1">loc &lt; instrlen </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">instring[loc].isspace() </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">col( loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring ) != self.col :</span>

3138         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">loc</span>

3142         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">thiscol &gt; self.col:</span>

3343 
3344         <span class="s0"># collapse nested And's of the form And( And( And( a,b), c), d) to And( a,b,c,d )</span>
3345         <span class="s0"># but only if there are no parse actions or resultsNames on the nested And's</span>
3346         <span class="s0"># (likewise for Or's and MatchFirst's)</span>
3347         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">( len(self.exprs) == </span><span class="s4">2 </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3348             <span class="s1">other = self.exprs[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
3349             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">( isinstance( other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.__class__ ) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
3350                   <span class="s3">not</span><span class="s1">(other.parseAction) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
3351                   <span class="s1">other.resultsName </span><span class="s3">is None and</span>
3352                   <span class="s3">not </span><span class="s1">other.debug ):</span>
3353                 <span class="s1">self.exprs = other.exprs[:] + [ self.exprs[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] ]</span>
3354                 <span class="s1">self.strRepr = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
3355                 <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty |= other.mayReturnEmpty</span>
3356                 <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError  |= other.mayIndexError</span>
3357 
3358             <span class="s1">other = self.exprs[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
3359             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">( isinstance( other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.__class__ ) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
3360                   <span class="s3">not</span><span class="s1">(other.parseAction) </span><span class="s3">and</span>
3361                   <span class="s1">other.resultsName </span><span class="s3">is None and</span>
3362                   <span class="s3">not </span><span class="s1">other.debug ):</span>
3363                 <span class="s1">self.exprs = self.exprs[:-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] + other.exprs[:]</span>
3364                 <span class="s1">self.strRepr = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
3365                 <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty |= other.mayReturnEmpty</span>
3366                 <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError  |= other.mayIndexError</span>
3367 
3368         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;Expected &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ _ustr(self)</span>

3387 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">And(ParseExpression):</span>
3388     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3389     Requires all given C{ParseExpression}s to be found in the given order. 
3390     Expressions may be separated by whitespace. 
3391     May be constructed using the C{'+'} operator. 
3392     May also be constructed using the C{'-'} operator, which will suppress backtracking.

3400         expr = integer(&quot;id&quot;) + name_expr(&quot;name&quot;) + integer(&quot;age&quot;)

3463 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Or(ParseExpression):</span>
3464     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3465     Requires that at least one C{ParseExpression} is found. 
3466     If two expressions match, the expression that matches the longest string will be used. 
3467     May be constructed using the C{'^'} operator. 
3468  
3469     Example:: 
3470         # construct Or using '^' operator 
3471          
3472         number = Word(nums) ^ Combine(Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums)) 
3473         print(number.searchString(&quot;123 3.1416 789&quot;)) 
3474     prints:: 
3475         [['123'], ['3.1416'], ['789']]

3484     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3485         <span class="s1">maxExcLoc = -</span><span class="s4">1</span>
3486         <span class="s1">maxException = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
3487         <span class="s1">matches = []</span>
3488         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs:</span>

3507                 <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3508                     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">e._parse( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions )</span>
3509                 <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseException </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">err:</span>
3510                     <span class="s1">err.__traceback__ = </span><span class="s3">None</span>

3542 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">MatchFirst(ParseExpression):</span>
3543     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3544     Requires that at least one C{ParseExpression} is found. 
3545     If two expressions match, the first one listed is the one that will match. 
3546     May be constructed using the C{'|'} operator. 
3547  
3548     Example:: 
3549         # construct MatchFirst using '|' operator 
3550          
3551         # watch the order of expressions to match 
3552         number = Word(nums) | Combine(Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums)) 
3553         print(number.searchString(&quot;123 3.1416 789&quot;)) #  Fail! -&gt; [['123'], ['3'], ['1416'], ['789']] 
3554  
3555         # put more selective expression first 
3556         number = Combine(Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums)) | Word(nums) 
3557         print(number.searchString(&quot;123 3.1416 789&quot;)) #  Better -&gt; [['123'], ['3.1416'], ['789']] 
3558     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

3560         <span class="s1">super(MatchFirst</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__(exprs</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">savelist)</span>
3561         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.exprs:</span>
3562             <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = any(e.mayReturnEmpty </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs)</span>

3577             <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">IndexError:</span>

3579                     <span class="s1">maxException = ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">len(instring)</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e.errmsg</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self)</span>
3580                     <span class="s1">maxExcLoc = len(instring)</span>
3581 
3582         <span class="s0"># only got here if no expression matched, raise exception for match that made it the furthest</span>
3583         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3584             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">maxException </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3585                 <span class="s1">maxException.msg = self.errmsg</span>
3586                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">maxException</span>

3588                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;no defined alternatives to match&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>
