3610 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Each(ParseExpression):</span>
3611     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3612     Requires all given C{ParseExpression}s to be found, but in any order. 
3613     Expressions may be separated by whitespace. 
3614     May be constructed using the C{'&amp;'} operator. 
3615  
3616     Example:: 
3617         color = oneOf(&quot;RED ORANGE YELLOW GREEN BLUE PURPLE BLACK WHITE BROWN&quot;) 
3618         shape_type = oneOf(&quot;SQUARE CIRCLE TRIANGLE STAR HEXAGON OCTAGON&quot;) 
3619         integer = Word(nums) 
3620         shape_attr = &quot;shape:&quot; + shape_type(&quot;shape&quot;) 
3621         posn_attr = &quot;posn:&quot; + Group(integer(&quot;x&quot;) + ',' + integer(&quot;y&quot;))(&quot;posn&quot;) 
3622         color_attr = &quot;color:&quot; + color(&quot;color&quot;) 
3623         size_attr = &quot;size:&quot; + integer(&quot;size&quot;) 
3624  
3625         # use Each (using operator '&amp;') to accept attributes in any order  
3626         # (shape and posn are required, color and size are optional) 
3627         shape_spec = shape_attr &amp; posn_attr &amp; Optional(color_attr) &amp; Optional(size_attr) 
3628  
3629         shape_spec.runTests(''' 
3630             shape: SQUARE color: BLACK posn: 100, 120 
3631             shape: CIRCLE size: 50 color: BLUE posn: 50,80 
3632             color:GREEN size:20 shape:TRIANGLE posn:20,40 
3633             ''' 
3634             ) 
3635     prints:: 
3636         shape: SQUARE color: BLACK posn: 100, 120 
3637         ['shape:', 'SQUARE', 'color:', 'BLACK', 'posn:', ['100', ',', '120']] 
3638         - color: BLACK 
3639         - posn: ['100', ',', '120'] 
3640           - x: 100 
3641           - y: 120 
3642         - shape: SQUARE 
3643  
3644  
3645         shape: CIRCLE size: 50 color: BLUE posn: 50,80 
3646         ['shape:', 'CIRCLE', 'size:', '50', 'color:', 'BLUE', 'posn:', ['50', ',', '80']] 
3647         - color: BLUE 
3648         - posn: ['50', ',', '80'] 
3649           - x: 50 
3650           - y: 80 
3651         - shape: CIRCLE 
3652         - size: 50 
3653  
3654  
3655         color: GREEN size: 20 shape: TRIANGLE posn: 20,40 
3656         ['color:', 'GREEN', 'size:', '20', 'shape:', 'TRIANGLE', 'posn:', ['20', ',', '40']] 
3657         - color: GREEN 
3658         - posn: ['20', ',', '40'] 
3659           - x: 20 
3660           - y: 40 
3661         - shape: TRIANGLE 
3662         - size: 20 
3663     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
3664     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">exprs</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">savelist = </span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3665         <span class="s1">super(Each</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__(exprs</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">savelist)</span>
3666         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = all(e.mayReturnEmpty </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs)</span>
3667         <span class="s1">self.skipWhitespace = </span><span class="s3">True</span>

3670     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
3671         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.initExprGroups:</span>
3672             <span class="s1">self.opt1map = dict((id(e.expr)</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">Optional))</span>
3673             <span class="s1">opt1 = [ e.expr </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">Optional) ]</span>
3674             <span class="s1">opt2 = [ e </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">e.mayReturnEmpty </span><span class="s3">and not </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">Optional)]</span>
3675             <span class="s1">self.optionals = opt1 + opt2</span>
3676             <span class="s1">self.multioptionals = [ e.expr </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ZeroOrMore) ]</span>
3677             <span class="s1">self.multirequired = [ e.expr </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">OneOrMore) ]</span>
3678             <span class="s1">self.required = [ e </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">(Optional</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ZeroOrMore</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">OneOrMore)) ]</span>
3679             <span class="s1">self.required += self.multirequired</span>

3682         <span class="s1">tmpReqd = self.required[:]</span>
3683         <span class="s1">tmpOpt  = self.optionals[:]</span>
3684         <span class="s1">matchOrder = []</span>
3685 
3686         <span class="s1">keepMatching = </span><span class="s3">True</span>

3688             <span class="s1">tmpExprs = tmpReqd + tmpOpt + self.multioptionals + self.multirequired</span>
3689             <span class="s1">failed = []</span>
3690             <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tmpExprs:</span>
3691                 <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3692                     <span class="s1">tmpLoc = e.tryParse( instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tmpLoc )</span>

3694                     <span class="s1">failed.append(e)</span>
3695                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
3696                     <span class="s1">matchOrder.append(self.opt1map.get(id(e)</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">e))</span>
3697                     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tmpReqd:</span>

3699                     <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tmpOpt:</span>
3700                         <span class="s1">tmpOpt.remove(e)</span>
3701             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(failed) == len(tmpExprs):</span>
3702                 <span class="s1">keepMatching = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
3703 
3704         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">tmpReqd:</span>
3705             <span class="s1">missing = </span><span class="s2">&quot;, &quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(_ustr(e) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tmpReqd)</span>
3706             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;Missing one or more required elements (%s)&quot; </span><span class="s1">% missing )</span>
3707 
3708         <span class="s0"># add any unmatched Optionals, in case they have default values defined</span>
3709         <span class="s1">matchOrder += [e </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">self.exprs </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(e</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">Optional) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">e.expr </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tmpOpt]</span>
3710 
3711         <span class="s1">resultlist = []</span>
3712         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">e </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">matchOrder:</span>
3713             <span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">results = e._parse(instring</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">doActions)</span>
3714             <span class="s1">resultlist.append(results)</span>
3715

3811 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">FollowedBy(ParseElementEnhance):</span>
3812     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3813     Lookahead matching of the given parse expression.  C{FollowedBy} 
3814     does I{not} advance the parsing position within the input string, it only 
3815     verifies that the specified parse expression matches at the current 
3816     position.  C{FollowedBy} always returns a null token list. 
3817  
3818     Example:: 
3819         # use FollowedBy to match a label only if it is followed by a ':' 
3820         data_word = Word(alphas) 
3821         label = data_word + FollowedBy(':') 
3822         attr_expr = Group(label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word, stopOn=label).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
3823          
3824         OneOrMore(attr_expr).parseString(&quot;shape: SQUARE color: BLACK posn: upper left&quot;).pprint() 
3825     prints:: 
3826         [['shape', 'SQUARE'], ['color', 'BLACK'], ['posn', 'upper left']]

3830         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = </span><span class="s3">True</span>

3901                     <span class="s1">tokens += tmptokens</span>

3907 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">OneOrMore(_MultipleMatch):</span>
3908     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
3909     Repetition of one or more of the given expression. 
3910      
3911     Parameters: 
3912      - expr - expression that must match one or more times 
3913      - stopOn - (default=C{None}) - expression for a terminating sentinel 
3914           (only required if the sentinel would ordinarily match the repetition  
3915           expression)           
3916  
3917     Example:: 
3918         data_word = Word(alphas) 
3919         label = data_word + FollowedBy(':') 
3920         attr_expr = Group(label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
3921  
3922         text = &quot;shape: SQUARE posn: upper left color: BLACK&quot; 
3923         OneOrMore(attr_expr).parseString(text).pprint()  # Fail! read 'color' as data instead of next label -&gt; [['shape', 'SQUARE color']] 
3924  
3925         # use stopOn attribute for OneOrMore to avoid reading label string as part of the data 
3926         attr_expr = Group(label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word, stopOn=label).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
3927         OneOrMore(attr_expr).parseString(text).pprint() # Better -&gt; [['shape', 'SQUARE'], ['posn', 'upper left'], ['color', 'BLACK']] 
3928          
3929         # could also be written as 
3930         (attr_expr * (1,)).parseString(text).pprint()

4045 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">SkipTo(ParseElementEnhance):</span>
4046     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4047     Token for skipping over all undefined text until the matched expression is found. 
4048  
4049     Parameters: 
4050      - expr - target expression marking the end of the data to be skipped 
4051      - include - (default=C{False}) if True, the target expression is also parsed  
4052           (the skipped text and target expression are returned as a 2-element list). 
4053      - ignore - (default=C{None}) used to define grammars (typically quoted strings and  
4054           comments) that might contain false matches to the target expression 
4055      - failOn - (default=C{None}) define expressions that are not allowed to be  
4056           included in the skipped test; if found before the target expression is found,  
4057           the SkipTo is not a match 
4058  
4059     Example:: 
4060         report = ''' 
4061             Outstanding Issues Report - 1 Jan 2000 
4062  
4063                # | Severity | Description                               |  Days Open 
4064             -----+----------+-------------------------------------------+----------- 
4065              101 | Critical | Intermittent system crash                 |          6 
4066               94 | Cosmetic | Spelling error on Login ('log|n')         |         14 
4067               79 | Minor    | System slow when running too many reports |         47 
4068             ''' 
4069         integer = Word(nums) 
4070         SEP = Suppress('|') 
4071         # use SkipTo to simply match everything up until the next SEP 
4072         # - ignore quoted strings, so that a '|' character inside a quoted string does not match 
4073         # - parse action will call token.strip() for each matched token, i.e., the description body 
4074         string_data = SkipTo(SEP, ignore=quotedString) 
4075         string_data.setParseAction(tokenMap(str.strip)) 
4076         ticket_expr = (integer(&quot;issue_num&quot;) + SEP  
4077                       + string_data(&quot;sev&quot;) + SEP  
4078                       + string_data(&quot;desc&quot;) + SEP  
4079                       + integer(&quot;days_open&quot;)) 
4080          
4081         for tkt in ticket_expr.searchString(report): 
4082             print tkt.dump() 
4083     prints:: 
4084         ['101', 'Critical', 'Intermittent system crash', '6'] 
4085         - days_open: 6 
4086         - desc: Intermittent system crash 
4087         - issue_num: 101 
4088         - sev: Critical 
4089         ['94', 'Cosmetic', &quot;Spelling error on Login ('log|n')&quot;, '14'] 
4090         - days_open: 14 
4091         - desc: Spelling error on Login ('log|n') 
4092         - issue_num: 94 
4093         - sev: Cosmetic 
4094         ['79', 'Minor', 'System slow when running too many reports', '47'] 
4095         - days_open: 47 
4096         - desc: System slow when running too many reports 
4097         - issue_num: 79 
4098         - sev: Minor 
4099     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4100     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">include=</span><span class="s3">False, </span><span class="s1">ignore=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">failOn=</span><span class="s3">None </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4101         <span class="s1">super( SkipTo</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self ).__init__( other )</span>
4102         <span class="s1">self.ignoreExpr = ignore</span>
4103         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
4104         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
4105         <span class="s1">self.includeMatch = include</span>
4106         <span class="s1">self.asList = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
4107         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(failOn</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">basestring):</span>
4108             <span class="s1">self.failOn = ParserElement._literalStringClass(failOn)</span>
4109         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4110             <span class="s1">self.failOn = failOn</span>
4111         <span class="s1">self.errmsg = </span><span class="s2">&quot;No match found for &quot;</span><span class="s1">+_ustr(self.expr)</span>
4112 
4113     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">parseImpl( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">doActions=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4114         <span class="s1">startloc = loc</span>
4115         <span class="s1">instrlen = len(instring)</span>
4116         <span class="s1">expr = self.expr</span>
4117         <span class="s1">expr_parse = self.expr._parse</span>
4118         <span class="s1">self_failOn_canParseNext = self.failOn.canParseNext </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.failOn </span><span class="s3">is not None else None</span>
4119         <span class="s1">self_ignoreExpr_tryParse = self.ignoreExpr.tryParse </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.ignoreExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None else None</span>
4120         
4121         <span class="s1">tmploc = loc</span>
4122         <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s1">tmploc &lt;= instrlen:</span>
4123             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self_failOn_canParseNext </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4124                 <span class="s0"># break if failOn expression matches</span>
4125                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self_failOn_canParseNext(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tmploc):</span>
4126                     <span class="s3">break</span>
4127

4129                 <span class="s0"># advance past ignore expressions</span>
4130                 <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4131                     <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4132                         <span class="s1">tmploc = self_ignoreExpr_tryParse(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tmploc)</span>
4133                     <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">ParseBaseException:</span>
4134                         <span class="s3">break</span>

4138             <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">(ParseException</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">IndexError):</span>
4139                 <span class="s0"># no match, advance loc in string</span>
4140                 <span class="s1">tmploc += </span><span class="s4">1</span>

4142                 <span class="s0"># matched skipto expr, done</span>

4147             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self.errmsg</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">self)</span>
4148 
4149         <span class="s0"># build up return values</span>
4150         <span class="s1">loc = tmploc</span>
4151         <span class="s1">skiptext = instring[startloc:loc]</span>
4152         <span class="s1">skipresult = ParseResults(skiptext)</span>
4153         
4154         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.includeMatch:</span>

4156             <span class="s1">skipresult += mat</span>
4157

4160 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Forward(ParseElementEnhance):</span>
4161     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4162     Forward declaration of an expression to be defined later - 
4163     used for recursive grammars, such as algebraic infix notation. 
4164     When the expression is known, it is assigned to the C{Forward} variable using the '&lt;&lt;' operator. 
4165  
4166     Note: take care when assigning to C{Forward} not to overlook precedence of operators. 
4167     Specifically, '|' has a lower precedence than '&lt;&lt;', so that:: 
4168         fwdExpr &lt;&lt; a | b | c 
4169     will actually be evaluated as:: 
4170         (fwdExpr &lt;&lt; a) | b | c 
4171     thereby leaving b and c out as parseable alternatives.  It is recommended that you 
4172     explicitly group the values inserted into the C{Forward}:: 
4173         fwdExpr &lt;&lt; (a | b | c) 
4174     Converting to use the '&lt;&lt;=' operator instead will avoid this problem. 
4175  
4176     See L{ParseResults.pprint} for an example of a recursive parser created using 
4177     C{Forward}. 
4178     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4179     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other=</span><span class="s3">None </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4180         <span class="s1">super(Forward</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__( other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">savelist=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">)</span>
4181 
4182     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__lshift__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other ):</span>
4183         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance( other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">basestring ):</span>
4184             <span class="s1">other = ParserElement._literalStringClass(other)</span>
4185         <span class="s1">self.expr = other</span>
4186         <span class="s1">self.strRepr = </span><span class="s3">None</span>
4187         <span class="s1">self.mayIndexError = self.expr.mayIndexError</span>
4188         <span class="s1">self.mayReturnEmpty = self.expr.mayReturnEmpty</span>
4189         <span class="s1">self.setWhitespaceChars( self.expr.whiteChars )</span>
4190         <span class="s1">self.skipWhitespace = self.expr.skipWhitespace</span>
4191         <span class="s1">self.saveAsList = self.expr.saveAsList</span>
4192         <span class="s1">self.ignoreExprs.extend(self.expr.ignoreExprs)</span>
4193         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">self</span>

4253 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Combine(TokenConverter):</span>
4254     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4255     Converter to concatenate all matching tokens to a single string. 
4256     By default, the matching patterns must also be contiguous in the input string; 
4257     this can be disabled by specifying C{'adjacent=False'} in the constructor. 
4258  
4259     Example:: 
4260         real = Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums) 
4261         print(real.parseString('3.1416')) # -&gt; ['3', '.', '1416'] 
4262         # will also erroneously match the following 
4263         print(real.parseString('3. 1416')) # -&gt; ['3', '.', '1416'] 
4264  
4265         real = Combine(Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums)) 
4266         print(real.parseString('3.1416')) # -&gt; ['3.1416'] 
4267         # no match when there are internal spaces 
4268         print(real.parseString('3. 1416')) # -&gt; Exception: Expected W:(0123...) 
4269     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4270     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">expr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">joinString=</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">adjacent=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4271         <span class="s1">super(Combine</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__( expr )</span>
4272         <span class="s0"># suppress whitespace-stripping in contained parse expressions, but re-enable it on the Combine itself</span>
4273         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">adjacent:</span>
4274             <span class="s1">self.leaveWhitespace()</span>
4275         <span class="s1">self.adjacent = adjacent</span>
4276         <span class="s1">self.skipWhitespace = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
4277         <span class="s1">self.joinString = joinString</span>
4278         <span class="s1">self.callPreparse = </span><span class="s3">True</span>

4297 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Group(TokenConverter):</span>
4298     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4299     Converter to return the matched tokens as a list - useful for returning tokens of C{L{ZeroOrMore}} and C{L{OneOrMore}} expressions. 
4300  
4301     Example:: 
4302         ident = Word(alphas) 
4303         num = Word(nums) 
4304         term = ident | num 
4305         func = ident + Optional(delimitedList(term)) 
4306         print(func.parseString(&quot;fn a,b,100&quot;))  # -&gt; ['fn', 'a', 'b', '100'] 
4307  
4308         func = ident + Group(Optional(delimitedList(term))) 
4309         print(func.parseString(&quot;fn a,b,100&quot;))  # -&gt; ['fn', ['a', 'b', '100']] 
4310     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

4313         <span class="s1">self.saveAsList = </span><span class="s3">True</span>

4316         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[ tokenlist ]</span>

4318 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Dict(TokenConverter):</span>
4319     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4320     Converter to return a repetitive expression as a list, but also as a dictionary. 
4321     Each element can also be referenced using the first token in the expression as its key. 
4322     Useful for tabular report scraping when the first column can be used as a item key. 
4323  
4324     Example:: 
4325         data_word = Word(alphas) 
4326         label = data_word + FollowedBy(':') 
4327         attr_expr = Group(label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
4328  
4329         text = &quot;shape: SQUARE posn: upper left color: light blue texture: burlap&quot; 
4330         attr_expr = (label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word, stopOn=label).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
4331          
4332         # print attributes as plain groups 
4333         print(OneOrMore(attr_expr).parseString(text).dump()) 
4334          
4335         # instead of OneOrMore(expr), parse using Dict(OneOrMore(Group(expr))) - Dict will auto-assign names 
4336         result = Dict(OneOrMore(Group(attr_expr))).parseString(text) 
4337         print(result.dump()) 
4338          
4339         # access named fields as dict entries, or output as dict 
4340         print(result['shape'])         
4341         print(result.asDict()) 
4342     prints:: 
4343         ['shape', 'SQUARE', 'posn', 'upper left', 'color', 'light blue', 'texture', 'burlap'] 
4344  
4345         [['shape', 'SQUARE'], ['posn', 'upper left'], ['color', 'light blue'], ['texture', 'burlap']] 
4346         - color: light blue 
4347         - posn: upper left 
4348         - shape: SQUARE 
4349         - texture: burlap 
4350         SQUARE 
4351         {'color': 'light blue', 'posn': 'upper left', 'texture': 'burlap', 'shape': 'SQUARE'} 
4352     See more examples at L{ParseResults} of accessing fields by results name. 
4353     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4354     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">__init__( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">expr ):</span>
4355         <span class="s1">super(Dict</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">self).__init__( expr )</span>
4356         <span class="s1">self.saveAsList = </span><span class="s3">True</span>
4357 
4358     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">postParse( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tokenlist ):</span>
4359         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">tok </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(tokenlist):</span>

4361                 <span class="s3">continue</span>

4363             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(ikey</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">int):</span>

4367             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">len(tok)==</span><span class="s4">2 </span><span class="s3">and not </span><span class="s1">isinstance(tok[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults):</span>
4368                 <span class="s1">tokenlist[ikey] = _ParseResultsWithOffset(tok[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">i)</span>
4369             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4370                 <span class="s1">dictvalue = tok.copy() </span><span class="s0">#ParseResults(i)</span>
4371                 <span class="s3">del </span><span class="s1">dictvalue[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
4372                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(dictvalue)!= </span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">(isinstance(dictvalue</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">dictvalue.haskeys()):</span>
4373                     <span class="s1">tokenlist[ikey] = _ParseResultsWithOffset(dictvalue</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">i)</span>
4374                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4375                     <span class="s1">tokenlist[ikey] = _ParseResultsWithOffset(dictvalue[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">i)</span>

4377         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">self.resultsName:</span>
4378             <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[ tokenlist ]</span>

4383 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">Suppress(TokenConverter):</span>
4384     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4385     Converter for ignoring the results of a parsed expression. 
4386  
4387     Example:: 
4388         source = &quot;a, b, c,d&quot; 
4389         wd = Word(alphas) 
4390         wd_list1 = wd + ZeroOrMore(',' + wd) 
4391         print(wd_list1.parseString(source)) 
4392  
4393         # often, delimiters that are useful during parsing are just in the 
4394         # way afterward - use Suppress to keep them out of the parsed output 
4395         wd_list2 = wd + ZeroOrMore(Suppress(',') + wd) 
4396         print(wd_list2.parseString(source)) 
4397     prints:: 
4398         ['a', ',', 'b', ',', 'c', ',', 'd'] 
4399         ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'] 
4400     (See also L{delimitedList}.) 
4401     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4402     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">postParse( self</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">instring</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tokenlist ):</span>
4403         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[]</span>

4405     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">suppress( self ):</span>

4425 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">traceParseAction(f):</span>
4426     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4427     Decorator for debugging parse actions.  
4428      
4429     When the parse action is called, this decorator will print C{&quot;&gt;&gt; entering I{method-name}(line:I{current_source_line}, I{parse_location}, I{matched_tokens})&quot;.} 
4430     When the parse action completes, the decorator will print C{&quot;&lt;&lt;&quot;} followed by the returned value, or any exception that the parse action raised. 
4431  
4432     Example:: 
4433         wd = Word(alphas) 
4434  
4435         @traceParseAction 
4436         def remove_duplicate_chars(tokens): 
4437             return ''.join(sorted(set(''.join(tokens)))) 
4438  
4439         wds = OneOrMore(wd).setParseAction(remove_duplicate_chars) 
4440         print(wds.parseString(&quot;slkdjs sld sldd sdlf sdljf&quot;)) 
4441     prints:: 
4442         &gt;&gt;entering remove_duplicate_chars(line: 'slkdjs sld sldd sdlf sdljf', 0, (['slkdjs', 'sld', 'sldd', 'sdlf', 'sdljf'], {})) 
4443         &lt;&lt;leaving remove_duplicate_chars (ret: 'dfjkls') 
4444         ['dfjkls'] 
4445     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4446     <span class="s1">f = _trim_arity(f)</span>
4447     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">z(*paArgs):</span>
4448         <span class="s1">thisFunc = f.__name__</span>
4449         <span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t = paArgs[-</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">:]</span>
4450         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(paArgs)&gt;</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4451             <span class="s1">thisFunc = paArgs[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].__class__.__name__ + </span><span class="s2">'.' </span><span class="s1">+ thisFunc</span>
4452         <span class="s1">sys.stderr.write( </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&gt;entering %s(line: '%s', %d, %r)</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (thisFunc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">line(l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s)</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t) )</span>
4453         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4454             <span class="s1">ret = f(*paArgs)</span>
4455         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">Exception </span><span class="s3">as </span><span class="s1">exc:</span>
4456             <span class="s1">sys.stderr.write( </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;&lt;leaving %s (exception: %s)</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (thisFunc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">exc) )</span>
4457             <span class="s3">raise</span>
4458         <span class="s1">sys.stderr.write( </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;&lt;leaving %s (ret: %r)</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot; </span><span class="s1">% (thisFunc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ret) )</span>
4459         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>
4460     <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4461         <span class="s1">z.__name__ = f.__name__</span>
4462     <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">AttributeError:</span>
4463         <span class="s3">pass</span>
4464     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">z</span>

4469 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">delimitedList( expr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">delim=</span><span class="s2">&quot;,&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">combine=</span><span class="s3">False </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4470     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4471     Helper to define a delimited list of expressions - the delimiter defaults to ','. 
4472     By default, the list elements and delimiters can have intervening whitespace, and 
4473     comments, but this can be overridden by passing C{combine=True} in the constructor. 
4474     If C{combine} is set to C{True}, the matching tokens are returned as a single token 
4475     string, with the delimiters included; otherwise, the matching tokens are returned 
4476     as a list of tokens, with the delimiters suppressed. 
4477  
4478     Example:: 
4479         delimitedList(Word(alphas)).parseString(&quot;aa,bb,cc&quot;) # -&gt; ['aa', 'bb', 'cc'] 
4480         delimitedList(Word(hexnums), delim=':', combine=True).parseString(&quot;AA:BB:CC:DD:EE&quot;) # -&gt; ['AA:BB:CC:DD:EE'] 
4481     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4482     <span class="s1">dlName = _ustr(expr)+</span><span class="s2">&quot; [&quot;</span><span class="s1">+_ustr(delim)+</span><span class="s2">&quot; &quot;</span><span class="s1">+_ustr(expr)+</span><span class="s2">&quot;]...&quot;</span>
4483     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">combine:</span>
4484         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Combine( expr + ZeroOrMore( delim + expr ) ).setName(dlName)</span>
4485     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4486         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">( expr + ZeroOrMore( Suppress( delim ) + expr ) ).setName(dlName)</span>

4488 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">countedArray( expr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">intExpr=</span><span class="s3">None </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4489     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4490     Helper to define a counted list of expressions. 
4491     This helper defines a pattern of the form:: 
4492         integer expr expr expr... 
4493     where the leading integer tells how many expr expressions follow. 
4494     The matched tokens returns the array of expr tokens as a list - the leading count token is suppressed. 
4495      
4496     If C{intExpr} is specified, it should be a pyparsing expression that produces an integer value. 
4497  
4498     Example:: 
4499         countedArray(Word(alphas)).parseString('2 ab cd ef')  # -&gt; ['ab', 'cd'] 
4500  
4501         # in this parser, the leading integer value is given in binary, 
4502         # '10' indicating that 2 values are in the array 
4503         binaryConstant = Word('01').setParseAction(lambda t: int(t[0], 2)) 
4504         countedArray(Word(alphas), intExpr=binaryConstant).parseString('10 ab cd ef')  # -&gt; ['ab', 'cd'] 
4505     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4506     <span class="s1">arrayExpr = Forward()</span>
4507     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">countFieldParseAction(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
4508         <span class="s1">n = t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
4509         <span class="s1">arrayExpr &lt;&lt; (n </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">Group(And([expr]*n)) </span><span class="s3">or </span><span class="s1">Group(empty))</span>
4510         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[]</span>
4511     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">intExpr </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4512         <span class="s1">intExpr = Word(nums).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t:int(t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]))</span>
4513     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4514         <span class="s1">intExpr = intExpr.copy()</span>
4515     <span class="s1">intExpr.setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;arrayLen&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4516     <span class="s1">intExpr.addParseAction(countFieldParseAction</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callDuringTry=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4517     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">( intExpr + arrayExpr ).setName(</span><span class="s2">'(len) ' </span><span class="s1">+ _ustr(expr) + </span><span class="s2">'...'</span><span class="s1">)</span>

4519 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_flatten(L):</span>
4520     <span class="s1">ret = []</span>
4521     <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">L:</span>

4523             <span class="s1">ret.extend(_flatten(i))</span>

4525             <span class="s1">ret.append(i)</span>

4528 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">matchPreviousLiteral(expr):</span>
4529     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4530     Helper to define an expression that is indirectly defined from 
4531     the tokens matched in a previous expression, that is, it looks 
4532     for a 'repeat' of a previous expression.  For example:: 
4533         first = Word(nums) 
4534         second = matchPreviousLiteral(first) 
4535         matchExpr = first + &quot;:&quot; + second 
4536     will match C{&quot;1:1&quot;}, but not C{&quot;1:2&quot;}.  Because this matches a 
4537     previous literal, will also match the leading C{&quot;1:1&quot;} in C{&quot;1:10&quot;}. 
4538     If this is not desired, use C{matchPreviousExpr}. 
4539     Do I{not} use with packrat parsing enabled. 
4540     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4541     <span class="s1">rep = Forward()</span>
4542     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">copyTokenToRepeater(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
4543         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">t:</span>
4544             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(t) == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4545                 <span class="s1">rep &lt;&lt; t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span>
4546             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4547                 <span class="s0"># flatten t tokens</span>
4548                 <span class="s1">tflat = _flatten(t.asList())</span>
4549                 <span class="s1">rep &lt;&lt; And(Literal(tt) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">tt </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">tflat)</span>
4550         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4551             <span class="s1">rep &lt;&lt; Empty()</span>
4552     <span class="s1">expr.addParseAction(copyTokenToRepeater</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callDuringTry=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4553     <span class="s1">rep.setName(</span><span class="s2">'(prev) ' </span><span class="s1">+ _ustr(expr))</span>
4554     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">rep</span>

4556 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">matchPreviousExpr(expr):</span>
4557     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4558     Helper to define an expression that is indirectly defined from 
4559     the tokens matched in a previous expression, that is, it looks 
4560     for a 'repeat' of a previous expression.  For example:: 
4561         first = Word(nums) 
4562         second = matchPreviousExpr(first) 
4563         matchExpr = first + &quot;:&quot; + second 
4564     will match C{&quot;1:1&quot;}, but not C{&quot;1:2&quot;}.  Because this matches by 
4565     expressions, will I{not} match the leading C{&quot;1:1&quot;} in C{&quot;1:10&quot;}; 
4566     the expressions are evaluated first, and then compared, so 
4567     C{&quot;1&quot;} is compared with C{&quot;10&quot;}. 
4568     Do I{not} use with packrat parsing enabled. 
4569     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4570     <span class="s1">rep = Forward()</span>
4571     <span class="s1">e2 = expr.copy()</span>
4572     <span class="s1">rep &lt;&lt;= e2</span>
4573     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">copyTokenToRepeater(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
4574         <span class="s1">matchTokens = _flatten(t.asList())</span>
4575         <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">mustMatchTheseTokens(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
4576             <span class="s1">theseTokens = _flatten(t.asList())</span>
4577             <span class="s3">if  </span><span class="s1">theseTokens != matchTokens:</span>
4578                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4579         <span class="s1">rep.setParseAction( mustMatchTheseTokens</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callDuringTry=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">)</span>
4580     <span class="s1">expr.addParseAction(copyTokenToRepeater</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">callDuringTry=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4581     <span class="s1">rep.setName(</span><span class="s2">'(prev) ' </span><span class="s1">+ _ustr(expr))</span>
4582     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">rep</span>

4584 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">_escapeRegexRangeChars(s):</span>
4585     <span class="s0">#~  escape these chars: ^-]</span>
4586     <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s2">r&quot;\^-]&quot;</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4587         <span class="s1">s = s.replace(c</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">_bslash+c)</span>
4588     <span class="s1">s = s.replace(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\n</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">r&quot;\n&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4589     <span class="s1">s = s.replace(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\t</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">r&quot;\t&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

4592 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">oneOf( strs</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">caseless=</span><span class="s3">False, </span><span class="s1">useRegex=</span><span class="s3">True </span><span class="s1">):</span>
4593     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4594     Helper to quickly define a set of alternative Literals, and makes sure to do 
4595     longest-first testing when there is a conflict, regardless of the input order, 
4596     but returns a C{L{MatchFirst}} for best performance. 
4597  
4598     Parameters: 
4599      - strs - a string of space-delimited literals, or a collection of string literals 
4600      - caseless - (default=C{False}) - treat all literals as caseless 
4601      - useRegex - (default=C{True}) - as an optimization, will generate a Regex 
4602           object; otherwise, will generate a C{MatchFirst} object (if C{caseless=True}, or 
4603           if creating a C{Regex} raises an exception) 
4604  
4605     Example:: 
4606         comp_oper = oneOf(&quot;&lt; = &gt; &lt;= &gt;= !=&quot;) 
4607         var = Word(alphas) 
4608         number = Word(nums) 
4609         term = var | number 
4610         comparison_expr = term + comp_oper + term 
4611         print(comparison_expr.searchString(&quot;B = 12  AA=23 B&lt;=AA AA&gt;12&quot;)) 
4612     prints:: 
4613         [['B', '=', '12'], ['AA', '=', '23'], ['B', '&lt;=', 'AA'], ['AA', '&gt;', '12']] 
4614     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4615     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">caseless:</span>
4616         <span class="s1">isequal = ( </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">a</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">b: a.upper() == b.upper() )</span>
4617         <span class="s1">masks = ( </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">a</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">b: b.upper().startswith(a.upper()) )</span>
4618         <span class="s1">parseElementClass = CaselessLiteral</span>
4619     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4620         <span class="s1">isequal = ( </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">a</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">b: a == b )</span>
4621         <span class="s1">masks = ( </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">a</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">b: b.startswith(a) )</span>
4622         <span class="s1">parseElementClass = Literal</span>
4623 
4624     <span class="s1">symbols = []</span>
4625     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(strs</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">basestring):</span>
4626         <span class="s1">symbols = strs.split()</span>
4627     <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">isinstance(strs</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">Iterable):</span>
4628         <span class="s1">symbols = list(strs)</span>
4629     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4630         <span class="s1">warnings.warn(</span><span class="s2">&quot;Invalid argument to oneOf, expected string or iterable&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
4631                 <span class="s1">SyntaxWarning</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">stacklevel=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4632     <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">symbols:</span>
4633         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">NoMatch()</span>
4634 
4635     <span class="s1">i = </span><span class="s4">0</span>
4636     <span class="s3">while </span><span class="s1">i &lt; len(symbols)-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4637         <span class="s1">cur = symbols[i]</span>
4638         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">j</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">other </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(symbols[i+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:]):</span>
4639             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">( isequal(other</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">cur) ):</span>
4640                 <span class="s3">del </span><span class="s1">symbols[i+j+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
4641                 <span class="s3">break</span>
4642             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">( masks(cur</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">other) ):</span>
4643                 <span class="s3">del </span><span class="s1">symbols[i+j+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]</span>
4644                 <span class="s1">symbols.insert(i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">other)</span>
4645                 <span class="s1">cur = other</span>
4646                 <span class="s3">break</span>
4647         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4648             <span class="s1">i += </span><span class="s4">1</span>
4649 
4650     <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">caseless </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">useRegex:</span>
4651         <span class="s0">#~ print (strs,&quot;-&gt;&quot;, &quot;|&quot;.join( [ _escapeRegexChars(sym) for sym in symbols] ))</span>
4652         <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4653             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(symbols)==len(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(symbols)):</span>
4654                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Regex( </span><span class="s2">&quot;[%s]&quot; </span><span class="s1">% </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(_escapeRegexRangeChars(sym) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">sym </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">symbols) ).setName(</span><span class="s2">' | '</span><span class="s1">.join(symbols))</span>
4655             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4656                 <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Regex( </span><span class="s2">&quot;|&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(re.escape(sym) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">sym </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">symbols) ).setName(</span><span class="s2">' | '</span><span class="s1">.join(symbols))</span>
4657         <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">Exception:</span>
4658             <span class="s1">warnings.warn(</span><span class="s2">&quot;Exception creating Regex for oneOf, building MatchFirst&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span>
4659                     <span class="s1">SyntaxWarning</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">stacklevel=</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4660 
4661 
4662     <span class="s0"># last resort, just use MatchFirst</span>
4663     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">MatchFirst(parseElementClass(sym) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">sym </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">symbols).setName(</span><span class="s2">' | '</span><span class="s1">.join(symbols))</span>

4665 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">dictOf( key</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">value ):</span>
4666     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4667     Helper to easily and clearly define a dictionary by specifying the respective patterns 
4668     for the key and value.  Takes care of defining the C{L{Dict}}, C{L{ZeroOrMore}}, and C{L{Group}} tokens 
4669     in the proper order.  The key pattern can include delimiting markers or punctuation, 
4670     as long as they are suppressed, thereby leaving the significant key text.  The value 
4671     pattern can include named results, so that the C{Dict} results can include named token 
4672     fields. 
4673  
4674     Example:: 
4675         text = &quot;shape: SQUARE posn: upper left color: light blue texture: burlap&quot; 
4676         attr_expr = (label + Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word, stopOn=label).setParseAction(' '.join)) 
4677         print(OneOrMore(attr_expr).parseString(text).dump()) 
4678          
4679         attr_label = label 
4680         attr_value = Suppress(':') + OneOrMore(data_word, stopOn=label).setParseAction(' '.join) 
4681  
4682         # similar to Dict, but simpler call format 
4683         result = dictOf(attr_label, attr_value).parseString(text) 
4684         print(result.dump()) 
4685         print(result['shape']) 
4686         print(result.shape)  # object attribute access works too 
4687         print(result.asDict()) 
4688     prints:: 
4689         [['shape', 'SQUARE'], ['posn', 'upper left'], ['color', 'light blue'], ['texture', 'burlap']] 
4690         - color: light blue 
4691         - posn: upper left 
4692         - shape: SQUARE 
4693         - texture: burlap 
4694         SQUARE 
4695         SQUARE 
4696         {'color': 'light blue', 'shape': 'SQUARE', 'posn': 'upper left', 'texture': 'burlap'} 
4697     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4698     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Dict( ZeroOrMore( Group ( key + value ) ) )</span>

4700 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">originalTextFor(expr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">asString=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>
4701     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4702     Helper to return the original, untokenized text for a given expression.  Useful to 
4703     restore the parsed fields of an HTML start tag into the raw tag text itself, or to 
4704     revert separate tokens with intervening whitespace back to the original matching 
4705     input text. By default, returns astring containing the original parsed text.   
4706         
4707     If the optional C{asString} argument is passed as C{False}, then the return value is a  
4708     C{L{ParseResults}} containing any results names that were originally matched, and a  
4709     single token containing the original matched text from the input string.  So if  
4710     the expression passed to C{L{originalTextFor}} contains expressions with defined 
4711     results names, you must set C{asString} to C{False} if you want to preserve those 
4712     results name values. 
4713  
4714     Example:: 
4715         src = &quot;this is test &lt;b&gt; bold &lt;i&gt;text&lt;/i&gt; &lt;/b&gt; normal text &quot; 
4716         for tag in (&quot;b&quot;,&quot;i&quot;): 
4717             opener,closer = makeHTMLTags(tag) 
4718             patt = originalTextFor(opener + SkipTo(closer) + closer) 
4719             print(patt.searchString(src)[0]) 
4720     prints:: 
4721         ['&lt;b&gt; bold &lt;i&gt;text&lt;/i&gt; &lt;/b&gt;'] 
4722         ['&lt;i&gt;text&lt;/i&gt;'] 
4723     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4724     <span class="s1">locMarker = Empty().setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">loc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t: loc)</span>
4725     <span class="s1">endlocMarker = locMarker.copy()</span>
4726     <span class="s1">endlocMarker.callPreparse = </span><span class="s3">False</span>
4727     <span class="s1">matchExpr = locMarker(</span><span class="s2">&quot;_original_start&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + expr + endlocMarker(</span><span class="s2">&quot;_original_end&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4728     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">asString:</span>
4729         <span class="s1">extractText = </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t: s[t._original_start:t._original_end]</span>
4730     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4731         <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">extractText(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
4732             <span class="s1">t[:] = [s[t.pop(</span><span class="s2">'_original_start'</span><span class="s1">):t.pop(</span><span class="s2">'_original_end'</span><span class="s1">)]]</span>
4733     <span class="s1">matchExpr.setParseAction(extractText)</span>
4734     <span class="s1">matchExpr.ignoreExprs = expr.ignoreExprs</span>
4735     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">matchExpr</span>

4744 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">locatedExpr(expr):</span>
4745     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4746     Helper to decorate a returned token with its starting and ending locations in the input string. 
4747     This helper adds the following results names: 
4748      - locn_start = location where matched expression begins 
4749      - locn_end = location where matched expression ends 
4750      - value = the actual parsed results 
4751  
4752     Be careful if the input text contains C{&lt;TAB&gt;} characters, you may want to call 
4753     C{L{ParserElement.parseWithTabs}} 
4754  
4755     Example:: 
4756         wd = Word(alphas) 
4757         for match in locatedExpr(wd).searchString(&quot;ljsdf123lksdjjf123lkkjj1222&quot;): 
4758             print(match) 
4759     prints:: 
4760         [[0, 'ljsdf', 5]] 
4761         [[8, 'lksdjjf', 15]] 
4762         [[18, 'lkkjj', 23]] 
4763     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4764     <span class="s1">locator = Empty().setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t: l)</span>
4765     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">Group(locator(</span><span class="s2">&quot;locn_start&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + expr(</span><span class="s2">&quot;value&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + locator.copy().leaveWhitespace()(</span><span class="s2">&quot;locn_end&quot;</span><span class="s1">))</span>

4782 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">srange(s):</span>
4783     <span class="s5">r&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4784     Helper to easily define string ranges for use in Word construction.  Borrows 
4785     syntax from regexp '[]' string range definitions:: 
4786         srange(&quot;[0-9]&quot;)   -&gt; &quot;0123456789&quot; 
4787         srange(&quot;[a-z]&quot;)   -&gt; &quot;abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz&quot; 
4788         srange(&quot;[a-z$_]&quot;) -&gt; &quot;abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz$_&quot; 
4789     The input string must be enclosed in []'s, and the returned string is the expanded 
4790     character set joined into a single string. 
4791     The values enclosed in the []'s may be: 
4792      - a single character 
4793      - an escaped character with a leading backslash (such as C{\-} or C{\]}) 
4794      - an escaped hex character with a leading C{'\x'} (C{\x21}, which is a C{'!'} character)  
4795          (C{\0x##} is also supported for backwards compatibility)  
4796      - an escaped octal character with a leading C{'\0'} (C{\041}, which is a C{'!'} character) 
4797      - a range of any of the above, separated by a dash (C{'a-z'}, etc.) 
4798      - any combination of the above (C{'aeiouy'}, C{'a-zA-Z0-9_$'}, etc.) 
4799     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4800     <span class="s1">_expanded = </span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">p: p </span><span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">isinstance(p</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ParseResults) </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s2">''</span><span class="s1">.join(unichr(c) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">range(ord(p[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">])</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">ord(p[</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">])+</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
4801     <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4802         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(_expanded(part) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">part </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">_reBracketExpr.parseString(s).body)</span>
4803     <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">Exception:</span>
4804         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span>

4810     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

4844 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">tokenMap(func</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*args):</span>
4845     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4846     Helper to define a parse action by mapping a function to all elements of a ParseResults list.If any additional  
4847     args are passed, they are forwarded to the given function as additional arguments after 
4848     the token, as in C{hex_integer = Word(hexnums).setParseAction(tokenMap(int, 16))}, which will convert the 
4849     parsed data to an integer using base 16. 
4850  
4851     Example (compare the last to example in L{ParserElement.transformString}:: 
4852         hex_ints = OneOrMore(Word(hexnums)).setParseAction(tokenMap(int, 16)) 
4853         hex_ints.runTests(''' 
4854             00 11 22 aa FF 0a 0d 1a 
4855             ''') 
4856          
4857         upperword = Word(alphas).setParseAction(tokenMap(str.upper)) 
4858         OneOrMore(upperword).runTests(''' 
4859             my kingdom for a horse 
4860             ''') 
4861  
4862         wd = Word(alphas).setParseAction(tokenMap(str.title)) 
4863         OneOrMore(wd).setParseAction(' '.join).runTests(''' 
4864             now is the winter of our discontent made glorious summer by this sun of york 
4865             ''') 
4866     prints:: 
4867         00 11 22 aa FF 0a 0d 1a 
4868         [0, 17, 34, 170, 255, 10, 13, 26] 
4869  
4870         my kingdom for a horse 
4871         ['MY', 'KINGDOM', 'FOR', 'A', 'HORSE'] 
4872  
4873         now is the winter of our discontent made glorious summer by this sun of york 
4874         ['Now Is The Winter Of Our Discontent Made Glorious Summer By This Sun Of York'] 
4875     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

4877         <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">[func(tokn</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">*args) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">tokn </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">t]</span>
4878 
4879     <span class="s3">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
4880         <span class="s1">func_name = getattr(func</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">'__name__'</span><span class="s3">, </span>
4881                             <span class="s1">getattr(func</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s2">'__class__'</span><span class="s1">).__name__)</span>
4882     <span class="s3">except </span><span class="s1">Exception:</span>
4883         <span class="s1">func_name = str(func)</span>
4884     <span class="s1">pa.__name__ = func_name</span>
4885 
4886     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">pa</span>

4907                 <span class="s1">Optional(</span><span class="s2">&quot;/&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">default=[</span><span class="s3">False</span><span class="s1">]).setResultsName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;empty&quot;</span><span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]==</span><span class="s2">'/'</span><span class="s1">) + Suppress(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

4909         <span class="s1">printablesLessRAbrack = </span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(c </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">printables </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4910         <span class="s1">tagAttrValue = quotedString.copy().setParseAction( removeQuotes ) | Word(printablesLessRAbrack)</span>
4911         <span class="s1">openTag = Suppress(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + tagStr(</span><span class="s2">&quot;tag&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + \</span>
4912                 <span class="s1">Dict(ZeroOrMore(Group( tagAttrName.setParseAction(downcaseTokens) + \</span>
4913                 <span class="s1">Optional( Suppress(</span><span class="s2">&quot;=&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + tagAttrValue ) ))) + \</span>
4914                 <span class="s1">Optional(</span><span class="s2">&quot;/&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">default=[</span><span class="s3">False</span><span class="s1">]).setResultsName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;empty&quot;</span><span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]==</span><span class="s2">'/'</span><span class="s1">) + Suppress(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4915     <span class="s1">closeTag = Combine(_L(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;/&quot;</span><span class="s1">) + tagStr + </span><span class="s2">&quot;&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
4916 
4917     <span class="s1">openTag = openTag.setResultsName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;start&quot;</span><span class="s1">+</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(resname.replace(</span><span class="s2">&quot;:&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot; &quot;</span><span class="s1">).title().split())).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;%s&gt;&quot; </span><span class="s1">% resname)</span>
4918     <span class="s1">closeTag = closeTag.setResultsName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;end&quot;</span><span class="s1">+</span><span class="s2">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">.join(resname.replace(</span><span class="s2">&quot;:&quot;</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot; &quot;</span><span class="s1">).title().split())).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;/%s&gt;&quot; </span><span class="s1">% resname)</span>
4919     <span class="s1">openTag.tag = resname</span>
4920     <span class="s1">closeTag.tag = resname</span>
4921     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">openTag</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">closeTag</span>

4923 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">makeHTMLTags(tagStr):</span>
4924     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4925     Helper to construct opening and closing tag expressions for HTML, given a tag name. Matches 
4926     tags in either upper or lower case, attributes with namespaces and with quoted or unquoted values. 
4927  
4928     Example:: 
4929         text = '&lt;td&gt;More info at the &lt;a href=&quot;http://pyparsing.wikispaces.com&quot;&gt;pyparsing&lt;/a&gt; wiki page&lt;/td&gt;' 
4930         # makeHTMLTags returns pyparsing expressions for the opening and closing tags as a 2-tuple 
4931         a,a_end = makeHTMLTags(&quot;A&quot;) 
4932         link_expr = a + SkipTo(a_end)(&quot;link_text&quot;) + a_end 
4933          
4934         for link in link_expr.searchString(text): 
4935             # attributes in the &lt;A&gt; tag (like &quot;href&quot; shown here) are also accessible as named results 
4936             print(link.link_text, '-&gt;', link.href) 
4937     prints:: 
4938         pyparsing -&gt; http://pyparsing.wikispaces.com 
4939     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4940     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">_makeTags( tagStr</span><span class="s3">, False </span><span class="s1">)</span>

4945     tags only in the given upper/lower case.

4948     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
4949     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">_makeTags( tagStr</span><span class="s3">, True </span><span class="s1">)</span>

4951 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">withAttribute(*args</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">**attrDict):</span>
4952     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
4953     Helper to create a validating parse action to be used with start tags created 
4954     with C{L{makeXMLTags}} or C{L{makeHTMLTags}}. Use C{withAttribute} to qualify a starting tag 
4955     with a required attribute value, to avoid false matches on common tags such as 
4956     C{&lt;TD&gt;} or C{&lt;DIV&gt;}. 
4957  
4958     Call C{withAttribute} with a series of attribute names and values. Specify the list 
4959     of filter attributes names and values as: 
4960      - keyword arguments, as in C{(align=&quot;right&quot;)}, or 
4961      - as an explicit dict with C{**} operator, when an attribute name is also a Python 
4962           reserved word, as in C{**{&quot;class&quot;:&quot;Customer&quot;, &quot;align&quot;:&quot;right&quot;}} 
4963      - a list of name-value tuples, as in ( (&quot;ns1:class&quot;, &quot;Customer&quot;), (&quot;ns2:align&quot;,&quot;right&quot;) ) 
4964     For attribute names with a namespace prefix, you must use the second form.  Attribute 
4965     names are matched insensitive to upper/lower case. 
4966         
4967     If just testing for C{class} (with or without a namespace), use C{L{withClass}}. 
4968  
4969     To verify that the attribute exists, but without specifying a value, pass 
4970     C{withAttribute.ANY_VALUE} as the value. 
4971  
4972     Example:: 
4973         html = ''' 
4974             &lt;div&gt; 
4975             Some text 
4976             &lt;div type=&quot;grid&quot;&gt;1 4 0 1 0&lt;/div&gt; 
4977             &lt;div type=&quot;graph&quot;&gt;1,3 2,3 1,1&lt;/div&gt; 
4978             &lt;div&gt;this has no type&lt;/div&gt; 
4979             &lt;/div&gt; 
4980                  
4981         ''' 
4982         div,div_end = makeHTMLTags(&quot;div&quot;) 
4983  
4984         # only match div tag having a type attribute with value &quot;grid&quot; 
4985         div_grid = div().setParseAction(withAttribute(type=&quot;grid&quot;)) 
4986         grid_expr = div_grid + SkipTo(div | div_end)(&quot;body&quot;) 
4987         for grid_header in grid_expr.searchString(html): 
4988             print(grid_header.body) 
4989          
4990         # construct a match with any div tag having a type attribute, regardless of the value 
4991         div_any_type = div().setParseAction(withAttribute(type=withAttribute.ANY_VALUE)) 
4992         div_expr = div_any_type + SkipTo(div | div_end)(&quot;body&quot;) 
4993         for div_header in div_expr.searchString(html): 
4994             print(div_header.body) 
4995     prints:: 
4996         1 4 0 1 0 
4997  
4998         1 4 0 1 0 
4999         1,3 2,3 1,1 
5000     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
5001     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">args:</span>
5002         <span class="s1">attrs = args[:]</span>
5003     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5004         <span class="s1">attrs = attrDict.items()</span>
5005     <span class="s1">attrs = [(k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v) </span><span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">k</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">v </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">attrs]</span>
5006     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">pa(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">tokens):</span>
5007         <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">attrName</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">attrValue </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">attrs:</span>
5008             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">attrName </span><span class="s3">not in </span><span class="s1">tokens:</span>
5009                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;no matching attribute &quot; </span><span class="s1">+ attrName)</span>
5010             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">attrValue != withAttribute.ANY_VALUE </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">tokens[attrName] != attrValue:</span>
5011                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;attribute '%s' has value '%s', must be '%s'&quot; </span><span class="s1">%</span>
5012                                             <span class="s1">(attrName</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">tokens[attrName]</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">attrValue))</span>
5013     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">pa</span>
5014 <span class="s1">withAttribute.ANY_VALUE = object()</span>

5016 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">withClass(classname</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">namespace=</span><span class="s2">''</span><span class="s1">):</span>
5017     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
5018     Simplified version of C{L{withAttribute}} when matching on a div class - made 
5019     difficult because C{class} is a reserved word in Python. 
5020  
5021     Example:: 
5022         html = ''' 
5023             &lt;div&gt; 
5024             Some text 
5025             &lt;div class=&quot;grid&quot;&gt;1 4 0 1 0&lt;/div&gt; 
5026             &lt;div class=&quot;graph&quot;&gt;1,3 2,3 1,1&lt;/div&gt; 
5027             &lt;div&gt;this &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; has no class&lt;/div&gt; 
5028             &lt;/div&gt; 
5029                  
5030         ''' 
5031         div,div_end = makeHTMLTags(&quot;div&quot;) 
5032         div_grid = div().setParseAction(withClass(&quot;grid&quot;)) 
5033          
5034         grid_expr = div_grid + SkipTo(div | div_end)(&quot;body&quot;) 
5035         for grid_header in grid_expr.searchString(html): 
5036             print(grid_header.body) 
5037          
5038         div_any_type = div().setParseAction(withClass(withAttribute.ANY_VALUE)) 
5039         div_expr = div_any_type + SkipTo(div | div_end)(&quot;body&quot;) 
5040         for div_header in div_expr.searchString(html): 
5041             print(div_header.body) 
5042     prints:: 
5043         1 4 0 1 0 
5044  
5045         1 4 0 1 0 
5046         1,3 2,3 1,1 
5047     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
5048     <span class="s1">classattr = </span><span class="s2">&quot;%s:class&quot; </span><span class="s1">% namespace </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">namespace </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s2">&quot;class&quot;</span>
5049     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">withAttribute(**{classattr : classname})        </span>
