5051 <span class="s1">opAssoc = _Constants()</span>
5052 <span class="s1">opAssoc.LEFT = object()</span>
5053 <span class="s1">opAssoc.RIGHT = object()</span>
5054 
5055 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">infixNotation( baseExpr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">opList</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">lpar=Suppress(</span><span class="s2">'('</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">rpar=Suppress(</span><span class="s2">')'</span><span class="s1">) ):</span>
5056     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
5057     Helper method for constructing grammars of expressions made up of 
5058     operators working in a precedence hierarchy.  Operators may be unary or 
5059     binary, left- or right-associative.  Parse actions can also be attached 
5060     to operator expressions. The generated parser will also recognize the use  
5061     of parentheses to override operator precedences (see example below). 
5062      
5063     Note: if you define a deep operator list, you may see performance issues 
5064     when using infixNotation. See L{ParserElement.enablePackrat} for a 
5065     mechanism to potentially improve your parser performance. 
5066  
5067     Parameters: 
5068      - baseExpr - expression representing the most basic element for the nested 
5069      - opList - list of tuples, one for each operator precedence level in the 
5070       expression grammar; each tuple is of the form 
5071       (opExpr, numTerms, rightLeftAssoc, parseAction), where: 
5072        - opExpr is the pyparsing expression for the operator; 
5073           may also be a string, which will be converted to a Literal; 
5074           if numTerms is 3, opExpr is a tuple of two expressions, for the 
5075           two operators separating the 3 terms 
5076        - numTerms is the number of terms for this operator (must 
5077           be 1, 2, or 3) 
5078        - rightLeftAssoc is the indicator whether the operator is 
5079           right or left associative, using the pyparsing-defined 
5080           constants C{opAssoc.RIGHT} and C{opAssoc.LEFT}. 
5081        - parseAction is the parse action to be associated with 
5082           expressions matching this operator expression (the 
5083           parse action tuple member may be omitted); if the parse action 
5084           is passed a tuple or list of functions, this is equivalent to 
5085           calling C{setParseAction(*fn)} (L{ParserElement.setParseAction}) 
5086      - lpar - expression for matching left-parentheses (default=C{Suppress('(')}) 
5087      - rpar - expression for matching right-parentheses (default=C{Suppress(')')}) 
5088  
5089     Example:: 
5090         # simple example of four-function arithmetic with ints and variable names 
5091         integer = pyparsing_common.signed_integer 
5092         varname = pyparsing_common.identifier  
5093          
5094         arith_expr = infixNotation(integer | varname, 
5095             [ 
5096             ('-', 1, opAssoc.RIGHT), 
5097             (oneOf('* /'), 2, opAssoc.LEFT), 
5098             (oneOf('+ -'), 2, opAssoc.LEFT), 
5099             ]) 
5100          
5101         arith_expr.runTests(''' 
5102             5+3*6 
5103             (5+3)*6 
5104             -2--11 
5105             ''', fullDump=False) 
5106     prints:: 
5107         5+3*6 
5108         [[5, '+', [3, '*', 6]]] 
5109  
5110         (5+3)*6 
5111         [[[5, '+', 3], '*', 6]] 
5112  
5113         -2--11 
5114         [[['-', 2], '-', ['-', 11]]] 
5115     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
5116     <span class="s1">ret = Forward()</span>
5117     <span class="s1">lastExpr = baseExpr | ( lpar + ret + rpar )</span>
5118     <span class="s3">for </span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">operDef </span><span class="s3">in </span><span class="s1">enumerate(opList):</span>
5119         <span class="s1">opExpr</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">arity</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">rightLeftAssoc</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">pa = (operDef + (</span><span class="s3">None,</span><span class="s1">))[:</span><span class="s4">4</span><span class="s1">]</span>
5120         <span class="s1">termName = </span><span class="s2">&quot;%s term&quot; </span><span class="s1">% opExpr </span><span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">arity &lt; </span><span class="s4">3 </span><span class="s3">else </span><span class="s2">&quot;%s%s term&quot; </span><span class="s1">% opExpr</span>
5121         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5122             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">opExpr </span><span class="s3">is None or </span><span class="s1">len(opExpr) != </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5123                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;if numterms=3, opExpr must be a tuple or list of two expressions&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5124             <span class="s1">opExpr1</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">opExpr2 = opExpr</span>
5125         <span class="s1">thisExpr = Forward().setName(termName)</span>
5126         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">rightLeftAssoc == opAssoc.LEFT:</span>
5127             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5128                 <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + opExpr) + Group( lastExpr + OneOrMore( opExpr ) )</span>
5129             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5130                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">opExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5131                     <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + opExpr + lastExpr) + Group( lastExpr + OneOrMore( opExpr + lastExpr ) )</span>
5132                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5133                     <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr+lastExpr) + Group( lastExpr + OneOrMore(lastExpr) )</span>
5134             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5135                 <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + opExpr1 + lastExpr + opExpr2 + lastExpr) + \</span>
5136                             <span class="s1">Group( lastExpr + opExpr1 + lastExpr + opExpr2 + lastExpr )</span>
5137             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5138                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;operator must be unary (1), binary (2), or ternary (3)&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5139         <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">rightLeftAssoc == opAssoc.RIGHT:</span>
5140             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5141                 <span class="s0"># try to avoid LR with this extra test</span>
5142                 <span class="s3">if not </span><span class="s1">isinstance(opExpr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">Optional):</span>
5143                     <span class="s1">opExpr = Optional(opExpr)</span>
5144                 <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(opExpr.expr + thisExpr) + Group( opExpr + thisExpr )</span>
5145             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5146                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">opExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5147                     <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + opExpr + thisExpr) + Group( lastExpr + OneOrMore( opExpr + thisExpr ) )</span>
5148                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5149                     <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + thisExpr) + Group( lastExpr + OneOrMore( thisExpr ) )</span>
5150             <span class="s3">elif </span><span class="s1">arity == </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5151                 <span class="s1">matchExpr = FollowedBy(lastExpr + opExpr1 + thisExpr + opExpr2 + thisExpr) + \</span>
5152                             <span class="s1">Group( lastExpr + opExpr1 + thisExpr + opExpr2 + thisExpr )</span>
5153             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5154                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;operator must be unary (1), binary (2), or ternary (3)&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5155         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5156             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;operator must indicate right or left associativity&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5157         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">pa:</span>
5158             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(pa</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">(tuple</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">list)):</span>
5159                 <span class="s1">matchExpr.setParseAction(*pa)</span>
5160             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5161                 <span class="s1">matchExpr.setParseAction(pa)</span>
5162         <span class="s1">thisExpr &lt;&lt;= ( matchExpr.setName(termName) | lastExpr )</span>
5163         <span class="s1">lastExpr = thisExpr</span>
5164     <span class="s1">ret &lt;&lt;= lastExpr</span>
5165     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>

5167 <span class="s1">operatorPrecedence = infixNotation</span>

5170 <span class="s1">dblQuotedString = Combine(Regex(</span><span class="s2">r'&quot;(?:[^&quot;\n\r\\]|(?:&quot;&quot;)|(?:\\(?:[^x]|x[0-9a-fA-F]+)))*'</span><span class="s1">)+</span><span class="s2">'&quot;'</span><span class="s1">).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;string enclosed in double quotes&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5171 <span class="s1">sglQuotedString = Combine(Regex(</span><span class="s2">r&quot;'(?:[^'\n\r\\]|(?:'')|(?:\\(?:[^x]|x[0-9a-fA-F]+)))*&quot;</span><span class="s1">)+</span><span class="s2">&quot;'&quot;</span><span class="s1">).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;string enclosed in single quotes&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5172 <span class="s1">quotedString = Combine(Regex(</span><span class="s2">r'&quot;(?:[^&quot;\n\r\\]|(?:&quot;&quot;)|(?:\\(?:[^x]|x[0-9a-fA-F]+)))*'</span><span class="s1">)+</span><span class="s2">'&quot;'</span><span class="s1">|</span>
5173                        <span class="s1">Regex(</span><span class="s2">r&quot;'(?:[^'\n\r\\]|(?:'')|(?:\\(?:[^x]|x[0-9a-fA-F]+)))*&quot;</span><span class="s1">)+</span><span class="s2">&quot;'&quot;</span><span class="s1">).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;quotedString using single or double quotes&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5174 <span class="s1">unicodeString = Combine(_L(</span><span class="s2">'u'</span><span class="s1">) + quotedString.copy()).setName(</span><span class="s2">&quot;unicode string literal&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

5176 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">nestedExpr(opener=</span><span class="s2">&quot;(&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">closer=</span><span class="s2">&quot;)&quot;</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">content=</span><span class="s3">None, </span><span class="s1">ignoreExpr=quotedString.copy()):</span>
5177     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
5178     Helper method for defining nested lists enclosed in opening and closing 
5179     delimiters (&quot;(&quot; and &quot;)&quot; are the default). 
5180  
5181     Parameters: 
5182      - opener - opening character for a nested list (default=C{&quot;(&quot;}); can also be a pyparsing expression 
5183      - closer - closing character for a nested list (default=C{&quot;)&quot;}); can also be a pyparsing expression 
5184      - content - expression for items within the nested lists (default=C{None}) 
5185      - ignoreExpr - expression for ignoring opening and closing delimiters (default=C{quotedString}) 
5186  
5187     If an expression is not provided for the content argument, the nested 
5188     expression will capture all whitespace-delimited content between delimiters 
5189     as a list of separate values. 
5190  
5191     Use the C{ignoreExpr} argument to define expressions that may contain 
5192     opening or closing characters that should not be treated as opening 
5193     or closing characters for nesting, such as quotedString or a comment 
5194     expression.  Specify multiple expressions using an C{L{Or}} or C{L{MatchFirst}}. 
5195     The default is L{quotedString}, but if no expressions are to be ignored, 
5196     then pass C{None} for this argument. 
5197  
5198     Example:: 
5199         data_type = oneOf(&quot;void int short long char float double&quot;) 
5200         decl_data_type = Combine(data_type + Optional(Word('*'))) 
5201         ident = Word(alphas+'_', alphanums+'_') 
5202         number = pyparsing_common.number 
5203         arg = Group(decl_data_type + ident) 
5204         LPAR,RPAR = map(Suppress, &quot;()&quot;) 
5205  
5206         code_body = nestedExpr('{', '}', ignoreExpr=(quotedString | cStyleComment)) 
5207  
5208         c_function = (decl_data_type(&quot;type&quot;)  
5209                       + ident(&quot;name&quot;) 
5210                       + LPAR + Optional(delimitedList(arg), [])(&quot;args&quot;) + RPAR  
5211                       + code_body(&quot;body&quot;)) 
5212         c_function.ignore(cStyleComment) 
5213          
5214         source_code = ''' 
5215             int is_odd(int x) {  
5216                 return (x%2);  
5217             } 
5218                  
5219             int dec_to_hex(char hchar) {  
5220                 if (hchar &gt;= '0' &amp;&amp; hchar &lt;= '9') {  
5221                     return (ord(hchar)-ord('0'));  
5222                 } else {  
5223                     return (10+ord(hchar)-ord('A')); 
5224                 }  
5225             } 
5226         ''' 
5227         for func in c_function.searchString(source_code): 
5228             print(&quot;%(name)s (%(type)s) args: %(args)s&quot; % func) 
5229  
5230     prints:: 
5231         is_odd (int) args: [['int', 'x']] 
5232         dec_to_hex (int) args: [['char', 'hchar']] 
5233     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
5234     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">opener == closer:</span>
5235         <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;opening and closing strings cannot be the same&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5236     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">content </span><span class="s3">is None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5237         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">isinstance(opener</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">basestring) </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">isinstance(closer</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">basestring):</span>
5238             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">len(opener) == </span><span class="s4">1 </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">len(closer)==</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5239                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ignoreExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5240                     <span class="s1">content = (Combine(OneOrMore(~ignoreExpr +</span>
5241                                     <span class="s1">CharsNotIn(opener+closer+ParserElement.DEFAULT_WHITE_CHARS</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
5242                                 <span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].strip()))</span>
5243                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5244                     <span class="s1">content = (empty.copy()+CharsNotIn(opener+closer+ParserElement.DEFAULT_WHITE_CHARS</span>
5245                                 <span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].strip()))</span>
5246             <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5247                 <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ignoreExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5248                     <span class="s1">content = (Combine(OneOrMore(~ignoreExpr + </span>
5249                                     <span class="s1">~Literal(opener) + ~Literal(closer) +</span>
5250                                     <span class="s1">CharsNotIn(ParserElement.DEFAULT_WHITE_CHARS</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
5251                                 <span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].strip()))</span>
5252                 <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5253                     <span class="s1">content = (Combine(OneOrMore(~Literal(opener) + ~Literal(closer) +</span>
5254                                     <span class="s1">CharsNotIn(ParserElement.DEFAULT_WHITE_CHARS</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">exact=</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
5255                                 <span class="s1">).setParseAction(</span><span class="s3">lambda </span><span class="s1">t:t[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">].strip()))</span>
5256         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5257             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ValueError(</span><span class="s2">&quot;opening and closing arguments must be strings if no content expression is given&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5258     <span class="s1">ret = Forward()</span>
5259     <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">ignoreExpr </span><span class="s3">is not None</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5260         <span class="s1">ret &lt;&lt;= Group( Suppress(opener) + ZeroOrMore( ignoreExpr | ret | content ) + Suppress(closer) )</span>
5261     <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5262         <span class="s1">ret &lt;&lt;= Group( Suppress(opener) + ZeroOrMore( ret | content )  + Suppress(closer) )</span>
5263     <span class="s1">ret.setName(</span><span class="s2">'nested %s%s expression' </span><span class="s1">% (opener</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">closer))</span>
5264     <span class="s3">return </span><span class="s1">ret</span>
5265 
5266 <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">indentedBlock(blockStatementExpr</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">indentStack</span><span class="s3">, </span><span class="s1">indent=</span><span class="s3">True</span><span class="s1">):</span>
5267     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
5268     Helper method for defining space-delimited indentation blocks, such as 
5269     those used to define block statements in Python source code. 
5270  
5271     Parameters: 
5272      - blockStatementExpr - expression defining syntax of statement that 
5273             is repeated within the indented block 
5274      - indentStack - list created by caller to manage indentation stack 
5275             (multiple statementWithIndentedBlock expressions within a single grammar 
5276             should share a common indentStack) 
5277      - indent - boolean indicating whether block must be indented beyond the 
5278             the current level; set to False for block of left-most statements 
5279             (default=C{True}) 
5280  
5281     A valid block must contain at least one C{blockStatement}. 
5282  
5283     Example:: 
5284         data = ''' 
5285         def A(z): 
5286           A1 
5287           B = 100 
5288           G = A2 
5289           A2 
5290           A3 
5291         B 
5292         def BB(a,b,c): 
5293           BB1 
5294           def BBA(): 
5295             bba1 
5296             bba2 
5297             bba3 
5298         C 
5299         D 
5300         def spam(x,y): 
5301              def eggs(z): 
5302                  pass 
5303         ''' 
5304  
5305  
5306         indentStack = [1] 
5307         stmt = Forward() 
5308  
5309         identifier = Word(alphas, alphanums) 
5310         funcDecl = (&quot;def&quot; + identifier + Group( &quot;(&quot; + Optional( delimitedList(identifier) ) + &quot;)&quot; ) + &quot;:&quot;) 
5311         func_body = indentedBlock(stmt, indentStack) 
5312         funcDef = Group( funcDecl + func_body ) 
5313  
5314         rvalue = Forward() 
5315         funcCall = Group(identifier + &quot;(&quot; + Optional(delimitedList(rvalue)) + &quot;)&quot;) 
5316         rvalue &lt;&lt; (funcCall | identifier | Word(nums)) 
5317         assignment = Group(identifier + &quot;=&quot; + rvalue) 
5318         stmt &lt;&lt; ( funcDef | assignment | identifier ) 
5319  
5320         module_body = OneOrMore(stmt) 
5321  
5322         parseTree = module_body.parseString(data) 
5323         parseTree.pprint() 
5324     prints:: 
5325         [['def', 
5326           'A', 
5327           ['(', 'z', ')'], 
5328           ':', 
5329           [['A1'], [['B', '=', '100']], [['G', '=', 'A2']], ['A2'], ['A3']]], 
5330          'B', 
5331          ['def', 
5332           'BB', 
5333           ['(', 'a', 'b', 'c', ')'], 
5334           ':', 
5335           [['BB1'], [['def', 'BBA', ['(', ')'], ':', [['bba1'], ['bba2'], ['bba3']]]]]], 
5336          'C', 
5337          'D', 
5338          ['def', 
5339           'spam', 
5340           ['(', 'x', 'y', ')'], 
5341           ':', 
5342           [[['def', 'eggs', ['(', 'z', ')'], ':', [['pass']]]]]]]  
5343     &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
5344     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">checkPeerIndent(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
5345         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">l &gt;= len(s): </span><span class="s3">return</span>
5346         <span class="s1">curCol = col(l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s)</span>
5347         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">curCol != indentStack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]:</span>
5348             <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">curCol &gt; indentStack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]:</span>
5349                 <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseFatalException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;illegal nesting&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5350             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;not a peer entry&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
5351 
5352     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">checkSubIndent(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
5353         <span class="s1">curCol = col(l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s)</span>
5354         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">curCol &gt; indentStack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">]:</span>
5355             <span class="s1">indentStack.append( curCol )</span>
5356         <span class="s3">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
5357             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;not a subentry&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

5359     <span class="s3">def </span><span class="s1">checkUnindent(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">t):</span>
5360         <span class="s3">if </span><span class="s1">l &gt;= len(s): </span><span class="s3">return</span>
5361         <span class="s1">curCol = col(l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">s)</span>
5362         <span class="s3">if not</span><span class="s1">(indentStack </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">curCol &lt; indentStack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">] </span><span class="s3">and </span><span class="s1">curCol &lt;= indentStack[-</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">]):</span>
5363             <span class="s3">raise </span><span class="s1">ParseException(s</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s1">l</span><span class="s3">,</span><span class="s2">&quot;not an unindent&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

5366     <span class="s1">NL = OneOrMore(LineEnd().setWhitespaceChars(</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s3">\t </span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="s1">).suppress())</span>

5369     <span class="s1">UNDENT = Empty().setParseAction(checkUnindent).setName(</span><span class="s2">'UNINDENT'</span><span class="s1">)</span>

5417 <span class="s0"># some other useful expressions - using lower-case class name since we are really using this as a namespace</span>
5418 <span class="s3">class </span><span class="s1">pyparsing_common:</span>
5419     <span class="s5">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
5420     Here are some common low-level expressions that may be useful in jump-starting parser development: 
5421      - numeric forms (L{integers&lt;integer&gt;}, L{reals&lt;real&gt;}, L{scientific notation&lt;sci_real&gt;}) 
5422      - common L{programming identifiers&lt;identifier&gt;} 
5423      - network addresses (L{MAC&lt;mac_address&gt;}, L{IPv4&lt;ipv4_address&gt;}, L{IPv6&lt;ipv6_address&gt;}) 
5424      - ISO8601 L{dates&lt;iso8601_date&gt;} and L{datetime&lt;iso8601_datetime&gt;} 
5425      - L{UUID&lt;uuid&gt;} 
5426      - L{comma-separated list&lt;comma_separated_list&gt;}

5428      - C{L{convertToInteger}} 
5429      - C{L{convertToFloat}} 
5430      - C{L{convertToDate}} 
5431      - C{L{convertToDatetime}} 
5432      - C{L{stripHTMLTags}} 
5433      - C{L{upcaseTokens}} 
5434      - C{L{downcaseTokens}} 
5435  
5436     Example:: 
5437         pyparsing_common.number.runTests(''' 
5438             # any int or real number, returned as the appropriate type 
5439             100 
5440             -100 
5441             +100 
5442             3.14159 
5443             6.02e23 
5444             1e-12 
5445             ''') 
5446  
5447         pyparsing_common.fnumber.runTests('''
